{"_id": "0adc25cfaa35147a", "name": "Insight of the Force", "type": "talent", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"prerequisites": "", "benefit": "You can make a Use the Force check in place of a Knowledge check for any Knowledge skill you are not Trained in. You are considered Trained in that Knowledge skill for the purposes of using this Talent. If you are entitled to a Knowledge check reroll, you can reroll your Use the Force check instead (subject to the same circumstances and limitations).", "description": {"value": "You can make a Use the Force check in place of a Knowledge check for any Knowledge skill you are not Trained in. You are considered Trained in that Knowledge skill for the purposes of using this Talent. If you are entitled to a Knowledge check reroll, you can reroll your Use the Force check instead (subject to the same circumstances and limitations)."}, "class": "fb5c2644f988e6bf", "costNumeric": null, "category": "Jedi Knight", "treeId": "152047d6ab7896ad", "tags": ["force", "jedi", "light-side", "skills"], "executionModel": "PASSIVE", "subType": "STATE", "abilityMeta": {"modifiers": [{"target": "attack", "value": 0, "type": "untyped", "predicates": [], "enabled": false, "priority": 500, "description": "[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Insight of the Force"}]}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"swse": {"id": "swse.talent.insight_of_the_force", "migratedToState": true, "migrationDate": "2026-03-08T18:22:17.403Z", "detectedPredicates": []}}}
{"_id": "0b04910aaabc51ba", "name": "Watch This", "type": "talent", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"prerequisites": "", "benefit": "You can move into or through a space occupied by a Vehicle of Colossal (Frigate) size or larger without causing a Collision. Additionally, if you Pilot a Colossal or smaller Vehicle, you can occupy the same space as a Vehicle of Colossal (Frigate) size or larger.", "description": {"value": "You can move into or through a space occupied by a Vehicle of Colossal (Frigate) size or larger without causing a Collision. Additionally, if you Pilot a Colossal or smaller Vehicle, you can occupy the same space as a Vehicle of Colossal (Frigate) size or larger."}, "class": "9c9989c34714f920", "costNumeric": null, "category": "Ace Pilot", "treeId": "296772ab8e69c9ef", "tags": ["action-economy", "controller", "defender", "evasion", "mobility", "piloting", "positioning", "precision", "scout", "skills", "social", "striker", "support"], "executionModel": "PASSIVE", "subType": "STATE", "abilityMeta": {"modifiers": [{"target": "defense.reflex", "value": 5, "type": "untyped", "predicates": ["defense.reflex", "attack.when-hit"], "enabled": true, "priority": 500, "description": "Watch This"}]}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"swse": {"id": "swse.talent.watch_this", "migratedToState": true, "migrationDate": "2026-03-08T18:22:17.403Z", "detectedPredicates": ["defense.reflex", "attack.when-hit"]}}}
{"_id": "0b18181b971fc505", "name": "Guardian Spirit", "type": "talent", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"prerequisites": "", "benefit": "You have a watching over you from the realm of The Force, providing you with insight and advice. Your might be an old mentor or an ancient member of your Force Tradition who has chosen to guide your Destiny. When you use the Search Your Feelings application of the Use the Force Skill, you can instead choose to consult your . When you do so, you learn more than just whether the results of your actions will be favorable or unfavorable; you also learn the nature of any immediate consequences, including potential encounters, and whether or not certain actions will bring you closer to achieving your Destiny. Additionally, you gain one bonus Force Point each day (available after you rest for at least 6 hours). This bonus Force Point can only be used to improve a Force Power or activate a Force Technique or a Force Secret. If you do not spend your bonus Force Point in a given day, it is lost at the start of the next day. You can spend a Force Point as a Swift Action to have your Guardian Spirit manifest for the duration of the encounter. Your Guardian Spirit appears in any square within 6 squares of you. A Guardian Spirit occupies a space, but creatures can move through the Guardian Spirit without obstruction. As long as the Guardian Spirit remains within 12 squares of you, you gain a +1 morale bonus on attack rolls, a +2 morale bonus on Use the Force checks, and a +2 morale bonus to your Will Defense. You can move the Guardian Spirit up to 6 squares as a Swift Action once per turn.", "description": "You have a watching over you from the realm of The Force, providing you with insight and advice. Your might be an old mentor or an ancient member of your Force Tradition who has chosen to guide your Destiny. When you use the Search Your Feelings application of the Use the Force Skill, you can instead choose to consult your . When you do so, you learn more than just whether the results of your actions will be favorable or unfavorable; you also learn the nature of any immediate consequences, including potential encounters, and whether or not certain actions will bring you closer to achieving your Destiny. Additionally, you gain one bonus Force Point each day (available after you rest for at least 6 hours). This bonus Force Point can only be used to improve a Force Power or activate a Force Technique or a Force Secret. If you do not spend your bonus Force Point in a given day, it is lost at the start of the next day. You can spend a Force Point as a Swift Action to have your Guardian Spirit manifest for the duration of the encounter. Your Guardian Spirit appears in any square within 6 squares of you. A Guardian Spirit occupies a space, but creatures can move through the Guardian Spirit without obstruction. As long as the Guardian Spirit remains within 12 squares of you, you gain a +1 morale bonus on attack rolls, a +2 morale bonus on Use the Force checks, and a +2 morale bonus to your Will Defense. You can move the Guardian Spirit up to 6 squares as a Swift Action once per turn.", "costNumeric": null, "treeId": "6629c34384c4ca53", "tags": ["action_economy", "ally_support", "controller", "defender", "force", "force_capacity", "force_control", "force_defense", "force_execution", "force_offense", "force_point_spend", "force_power_synergy", "guardian_spirit", "healing", "leader", "mobility", "new_option", "overwatch", "positioning", "resource_spend", "scaling", "scout", "skills", "striker", "support", "swift_action", "tree_6629c34384c4ca53", "uncategorized_talent", "use_the_force"], "executionModel": "PASSIVE", "subType": "MODIFIER", "abilityMeta": {"modifiers": [{"target": "defense.will", "type": "untyped", "value": 1, "enabled": true, "priority": 500, "description": "Migrated from AE system.defenses.will"}]}}, "effects": [{"_id": "36f736d1-020d-46ca-90a3-e2e3d4210df7", "name": "Guardian Spirit", "icon": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "changes": [{"key": "system.defenses.will", "mode": 2, "value": "1"}], "disabled": true, "duration": {}, "flags": {"swse": {"source": "talent", "talentName": "Guardian Spirit", "migratedToPassive": true}}}], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"swse": {"id": "swse.talent.guardian_spirit"}}}
{"_id": "0b2c53ed53f20751", "name": "Unrelenting Assault", "type": "talent", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"prerequisites": "Melee Smash", "benefit": "You launch yourself at your foe, attacking with weapons, limbs, or anything else available. Whenever you miss with a melee attack or the attack is negated, you still deal your Strength bonus in damage to the target (minimum 1), or 2 x your Strength bonus if you attack with a weapon you are wielding two-handed.", "description": {"value": "You launch yourself at your foe, attacking with weapons, limbs, or anything else available. Whenever you miss with a melee attack or the attack is negated, you still deal your Strength bonus in damage to the target (minimum 1), or 2 x your Strength bonus if you attack with a weapon you are wielding two-handed."}, "class": "f62ca2e639cab614", "costNumeric": null, "category": "Soldier", "prerequisitesStructured": {"type": "all", "conditions": [{"type": "talent", "id": "swse.talent.melee_smash"}], "_source": "canonical-csv"}, "treeId": "67fdd8dce9abd6c1", "tags": ["feat-chain", "melee", "soldier", "striker", "talent-chain"], "executionModel": "PASSIVE", "subType": "STATE", "abilityMeta": {"modifiers": [{"target": "attack", "value": 2, "type": "untyped", "predicates": ["attack.with-melee"], "enabled": true, "priority": 500, "description": "Unrelenting Assault"}]}}, "effects": [{"_id": "93a533bd-1250-47d5-8782-55fd0ed60869", "name": "Unrelenting Assault", "icon": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "changes": [{"key": "system.attacks.reroll", "mode": 5, "value": "true"}], "disabled": false, "duration": {}, "flags": {"swse": {"source": "talent", "talentName": "Unrelenting Assault"}}}], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"swse": {"id": "swse.talent.unrelenting_assault", "migratedToState": true, "migrationDate": "2026-03-08T18:22:17.403Z", "detectedPredicates": ["attack.with-melee"]}}}
{"_id": "0b3f4075ed84aee0", "name": "Ataru", "type": "talent", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"prerequisites": "", "benefit": "You may add your Dexterity bonus (instead of your Strength bonus) on damage rolls when wielding a Lightsaber. When you wield a Lightsaber two-handed, you may apply double your Dexterity bonus (instead of double your Strength bonus) to the damage.", "description": {"value": "You may add your Dexterity bonus (instead of your Strength bonus) on damage rolls when wielding a Lightsaber. When you wield a Lightsaber two-handed, you may apply double your Dexterity bonus (instead of double your Strength bonus) to the damage."}, "class": "fb5c2644f988e6bf", "costNumeric": null, "category": "Jedi Knight", "treeId": "2bc2572e852832e4", "tags": ["jedi", "lightsaber", "melee", "striker"], "executionModel": "PASSIVE", "subType": "STATE", "abilityMeta": {"modifiers": [{"target": "attack", "value": 0, "type": "untyped", "predicates": [], "enabled": false, "priority": 500, "description": "[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Ataru"}]}}, "effects": [{"_id": "51d31037-d4be-4c4d-a5e5-b405e21aa08a", "name": "Ataru - Apply DEX to Damage", "icon": "icons/svg/wind.svg", "changes": [{"key": "system.abilities.dex.applyToDamage", "mode": 5, "value": "true", "priority": 20}], "disabled": false, "duration": {}, "flags": {"swse": {"source": "talent", "talentName": "Ataru"}}}], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"swse": {"id": "swse.talent.ataru", "migratedToState": true, "migrationDate": "2026-03-08T18:22:17.403Z", "detectedPredicates": []}}}
{"_id": "0bbfcac85b09416a", "name": "Siang Lance Mastery", "type": "talent", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"prerequisites": "", "description": "Base Attack Bonus +7 You can spend a Force Point to empower a Siang Lance, which takes a Full-Round Action. After the Siang Lance in empowered, it deals an additional die of damage when you wield it. Others who wield the weapon do not gain the bonus damage die. Once per turn as a Reaction, you can gain a +2 deflection bonus to your Reflex Defense against any one ranged attack. To use this Talent, you must be wearing an active Shield Gauntlet, you must be aware of the attack, and you must not be Flat-Footed.", "benefit": "Base Attack Bonus +7 You can spend a Force Point to empower a Siang Lance, which takes a Full-Round Action. After the Siang Lance in empowered, it deals an additional die of damage when you wield it. Others who wield the weapon do not gain the bonus damage die. Once per turn as a Reaction, you can gain a +2 deflection bonus to your Reflex Defense against any one ranged attack. To use this Talent, you must be wearing an active Shield Gauntlet, you must be aware of the attack, and you must not be Flat-Footed.", "class": "", "category": "", "costNumeric": null, "treeId": "2a1838832f6146e2", "tags": ["action_economy", "block", "controller", "defender", "defense", "deflect", "duelist", "force", "force_defense", "force_offense", "force_point_spend", "lightsaber_polearm", "melee_defense", "offense_ranged", "positioning", "ranged", "reaction", "resource_spend", "shield", "shields", "striker", "sustained_damage", "tree_2a1838832f6146e2", "uncategorized_talent"], "executionModel": "PASSIVE", "subType": "STATE", "abilityMeta": {"modifiers": [{"target": "defense.reflex", "value": 7, "type": "untyped", "predicates": ["defense.against-ranged", "defense.reflex", "attack.with-ranged"], "enabled": true, "priority": 500, "description": "Siang Lance Mastery"}]}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"swse": {"migratedToState": true, "migrationDate": "2026-03-08T18:22:17.403Z", "detectedPredicates": ["defense.against-ranged", "defense.reflex", "attack.with-ranged"]}}}
{"_id": "0bc102751285d17c", "name": "Defensive Acuity", "type": "talent", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"prerequisites": "", "benefit": "When you take the Fight Defensively Action, you deal +1 die of damage with Lightsaber attacks and gain a +2 circumstance bonus on Use the Force checks made to negate an attack with the Block or Deflect Talents. These benefits last until the end of your next turn.", "description": {"value": "When you take the Fight Defensively Action, you deal +1 die of damage with Lightsaber attacks and gain a +2 circumstance bonus on Use the Force checks made to negate an attack with the Block or Deflect Talents. These benefits last until the end of your next turn."}, "class": "fec1f8af44fcc35a", "costNumeric": null, "category": "Jedi", "treeId": "10c843cef8ce2798", "tags": ["force", "force-defense", "force-offense", "jedi", "light-side", "lightsaber", "melee", "striker"], "executionModel": "PASSIVE", "subType": "STATE", "abilityMeta": {"modifiers": [{"target": "attack", "value": 0, "type": "untyped", "predicates": [], "enabled": false, "priority": 500, "description": "[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Defensive Acuity"}]}}, "effects": [{"_id": "5927b1c4-333c-4583-ac94-6c894d418a61", "name": "Defensive Acuity", "icon": "icons/svg/sword.svg", "changes": [{"key": "system.damage.lightsaber", "mode": 2, "value": "1d6"}], "disabled": false, "duration": {}, "flags": {"swse": {"source": "talent", "talentName": "Defensive Acuity"}}}], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"swse": {"id": "swse.talent.defensive_acuity", "migratedToState": true, "migrationDate": "2026-03-08T18:22:17.403Z", "detectedPredicates": []}}}
{"_id": "0be2881047fe9919", "name": "Blind Spot", "type": "talent", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"prerequisites": "", "benefit": "You can fly a Vehicle you Pilot so close to a target at least two sizes larger than your Vehicle that it is difficult for the target to avoid or attack you. You must be adjacent to the target (at Starship Scale) to use this Talent.", "description": {"value": "You can fly a Vehicle you Pilot so close to a target at least two sizes larger than your Vehicle that it is difficult for the target to avoid or attack you. You must be adjacent to the target (at Starship Scale) to use this Talent.\n\nAs a Swift Action, make an opposed Pilot check against the target. If you succeed, you move into the same space as your target. You move with your target if it moves (assuming your Vehicle has sufficient Speed to keep up), and you must make another opposed Pilot check each round as a Swift Action to stay in its Blind Spot.\n\nAs long as you stay in the target's Blind Spot, any attack you make against the target gains a +2 bonus, and the target takes a -2 penalty on attacks made against you."}, "class": "9c9989c34714f920", "costNumeric": null, "category": "Ace Pilot", "treeId": "b17c1515c06361d6", "tags": ["action-economy", "controller", "damage-reduction", "defender", "evasion", "leader", "mobility", "piloting", "positioning", "precision", "scout", "skills", "striker", "support", "sustained-damage"], "executionModel": "PASSIVE", "subType": "STATE", "abilityMeta": {"modifiers": [{"target": "defense.reflex", "value": 2, "type": "untyped", "predicates": ["defense.reflex", "attack.when-hit", "movement.while-moving", "proximity.ally-nearby"], "enabled": true, "priority": 500, "description": "Blind Spot"}]}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"swse": {"id": "swse.talent.blind_spot", "migratedToState": true, "migrationDate": "2026-03-08T18:22:17.403Z", "detectedPredicates": ["defense.reflex", "attack.when-hit", "movement.while-moving", "proximity.ally-nearby"]}}}
{"_id": "0bf26c4fb8622e0b", "name": "Armored Spacer", "type": "talent", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"prerequisites": "", "benefit": "You can use Armored Space Suits as if you had the Armor Proficiency (Heavy) Feat.", "description": {"value": "You can use Armored Space Suits as if you had the Armor Proficiency (Heavy) Feat."}, "class": "fcf8cc428a6eb01a", "costNumeric": null, "category": "Master Privateer", "treeId": "df6678946610c554", "tags": ["armor", "defender", "scoundrel"], "executionModel": "PASSIVE", "subType": "STATE", "abilityMeta": {"modifiers": [{"target": "attack", "value": 0, "type": "untyped", "predicates": [], "enabled": false, "priority": 500, "description": "[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Armored Spacer"}]}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"swse": {"skillSubstitution": true, "substitutionType": "armor_as_heavy", "description": "Your armor proficiency is treated as heavy armor proficiency", "id": "swse.talent.armored_spacer", "migratedToState": true, "migrationDate": "2026-03-08T18:22:17.403Z", "detectedPredicates": []}}}
{"_id": "0c5026168620dbae", "name": "Vehicle Sneak", "type": "talent", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"prerequisites": "Trained in Pilot", "benefit": "You know how to fly and operate your Vehicle in order to hide its approach visually, decrease the noise it produces, and minimize its sensor signature. Treat your ship as two size categories smaller when attempting Stealth checks.", "description": {"value": "You know how to fly and operate your Vehicle in order to hide its approach visually, decrease the noise it produces, and minimize its sensor signature. Treat your ship as two size categories smaller when attempting Stealth checks."}, "class": "b5bed5d1b5f42958", "costNumeric": null, "category": "Scout", "prerequisitesStructured": {"type": "all", "conditions": [{"type": "skillTrained", "skill": "b8dad0c963f046c6"}], "_source": "fix5F-canonical"}, "treeId": "089933380b40ce20", "tags": ["feat-chain", "precision", "scout", "skills", "stealth", "talent-chain"], "executionModel": "PASSIVE", "subType": "STATE", "abilityMeta": {"modifiers": [{"target": "attack", "value": 0, "type": "untyped", "predicates": [], "enabled": false, "priority": 500, "description": "[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Vehicle Sneak"}]}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"swse": {"id": "swse.talent.vehicle_sneak", "migratedToState": true, "migrationDate": "2026-03-08T18:22:17.403Z", "detectedPredicates": []}}}
{"_id": "0c636cdbb63cdba3", "name": "Greater Force Talisman", "type": "talent", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"prerequisites": "Force Talisman", "benefit": "You may spend a Force Point to imbue a weapon or some other portable object with The Force, creating a Talisman that provides protection to you. Creating the Talisman takes a Full-Round Action.", "description": {"value": "You may spend a Force Point to imbue a weapon or some other portable object with The Force, creating a Talisman that provides protection to you. Creating the Talisman takes a Full-Round Action.\n\nWhile you wear or carry the Talisman on your person, you gain a +1 Force bonus to all of your Defenses (Reflex Defense, Fortitude Defense, and Will Defense).\n\nYou may only have one Greater Force Talisman active at a given time, and if your Greater Force Talisman is destroyed, you may not create another Greater Force Talisman (or regular Force Talisman) for 24 hours."}, "class": "289fcf920ef0e184", "costNumeric": null, "category": "Force Adept", "prerequisitesStructured": {"type": "all", "conditions": [{"type": "talent", "id": "swse.talent.force_talisman"}], "_source": "canonical-csv"}, "treeId": "01e443d93e47f9c4", "tags": ["alchemy", "category_force_adept", "controller", "crafting", "empowerment", "force", "force_capacity", "force_execution", "force_point_spend", "force_training", "mystic", "resource_spend", "tree_01e443d93e47f9c4"], "executionModel": "PASSIVE", "subType": "MODIFIER", "abilityMeta": {"modifiers": [{"target": "defense.fortitude", "type": "untyped", "value": 1, "enabled": true, "priority": 500, "description": "Migrated from AE system.defenses.all"}, {"target": "defense.reflex", "type": "untyped", "value": 1, "enabled": true, "priority": 500, "description": "Migrated from AE system.defenses.all"}, {"target": "defense.will", "type": "untyped", "value": 1, "enabled": true, "priority": 500, "description": "Migrated from AE system.defenses.all"}]}}, "effects": [{"_id": "668abf60-aa52-47c8-afe4-60c8bed3a609", "name": "Greater Force Talisman", "icon": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "changes": [{"key": "system.defenses.all", "mode": 2, "value": "1"}], "disabled": true, "duration": {}, "flags": {"swse": {"source": "talent", "talentName": "Greater Force Talisman", "migratedToPassive": true}}}], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"swse": {"id": "swse.talent.greater_force_talisman"}}}
{"_id": "0c9b0788ad42450c", "name": "Extended Critical Range", "type": "talent", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"prerequisites": "", "description": "If you have another ability that increases your weapon's critical range against that target (such as the Elite Trooper's Talent, or the Jedi Knight's Vaapad Talent), you increase this range by 1 (for example, from 19-20 to 18-20). However, anything other than a Natural 20 is not considered an automatic hit; if you roll anything other than a Natural 20 and still miss the target, you do not score a Critical Hit.", "benefit": "If you have another ability that increases your weapon's critical range against that target (such as the Elite Trooper's Talent, or the Jedi Knight's Vaapad Talent), you increase this range by 1 (for example, from 19-20 to 18-20). However, anything other than a Natural 20 is not considered an automatic hit; if you roll anything other than a Natural 20 and still miss the target, you do not score a Critical Hit.", "class": "", "category": "", "costNumeric": null, "treeId": "d20682671d035cef", "tags": ["critical_hit", "force", "investigation", "knowledge", "light_side", "positioning", "precision", "resources", "social", "social_network", "striker", "tree_d20682671d035cef", "uncategorized_talent"], "executionModel": "PASSIVE", "subType": "STATE", "abilityMeta": {"modifiers": [{"target": "attack", "value": 2, "type": "untyped", "predicates": ["attack.when-hit"], "enabled": true, "priority": 500, "description": "Extended Critical Range"}]}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"swse": {"migratedToState": true, "migrationDate": "2026-03-08T18:22:17.403Z", "detectedPredicates": ["attack.when-hit"]}}}
{"_id": "0cdd50aaa65e4360", "name": "Voices", "type": "talent", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"prerequisites": "", "description": "You have learned to challenge your Midi-chlorians. If you succeed, you force them to obey your commands for a change. If you fail, your Use the Force modifier suffers. Once per encounter, as a swift action, roll 1d20 + your Character Level against your own Force Defense. Apply the result as a modifier to your Use the Force checks. Prerequisites: , Midi-chlorian Challenge Control! Control! You're finally learning Control! As a Free Action, you may add +5 to your Force Defense or your own rolls versus your own Force Defense during the encounter. Prerequisites: , Midi-chlorian Challenge, Midi-chlorian Control You're learning to follow your own path. You may reroll any Midi-chlorian check and may take the better result. Prerequisites: , Midi-chlorian Challenge, Midi-chlorian Control Now YOU are the Master. If you receive a Midi-chlorian request, you may ignore it and still receive the temporary Force Point.", "benefit": "You have learned to challenge your Midi-chlorians. If you succeed, you force them to obey your commands for a change. If you fail, your Use the Force modifier suffers. Once per encounter, as a swift action, roll 1d20 + your Character Level against your own Force Defense. Apply the result as a modifier to your Use the Force checks. Prerequisites: , Midi-chlorian Challenge Control! Control! You're finally learning Control! As a Free Action, you may add +5 to your Force Defense or your own rolls versus your own Force Defense during the encounter. Prerequisites: , Midi-chlorian Challenge, Midi-chlorian Control You're learning to follow your own path. You may reroll any Midi-chlorian check and may take the better result. Prerequisites: , Midi-chlorian Challenge, Midi-chlorian Control Now YOU are the Master. If you receive a Midi-chlorian request, you may ignore it and still receive the temporary Force Point.", "clas