{"_id": "35cbdbe9c91ba1d0", "name": "Skilled Advisor", "type": "talent", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"prerequisites": "", "benefit": "You can spend a Full-Round Action advising an ally, thereby granting them a +5 bonus on their next Skill Check. If you spend a Force Point, the bonus increases to +10. The target must be able to (and willing) to hear and understand your voice. You cannot advise yourself. This is a Mind-Affecting effect.", "description": {"value": "You can spend a Full-Round Action advising an ally, thereby granting them a +5 bonus on their next Skill Check. If you spend a Force Point, the bonus increases to +10. The target must be able to (and willing) to hear and understand your voice. You cannot advise yourself. This is a Mind-Affecting effect."}, "class": "fec1f8af44fcc35a", "costNumeric": null, "category": "Jedi", "treeId": "152047d6ab7896ad", "tags": ["action-economy", "force", "jedi", "light-side", "mobility", "positioning", "striker", "support"], "executionModel": "PASSIVE", "subType": "STATE", "abilityMeta": {"modifiers": [{"target": "skill", "value": 2, "type": "untyped", "predicates": ["proximity.ally-nearby"], "enabled": true, "priority": 500, "description": "Skilled Advisor"}]}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"swse": {"id": "swse.talent.skilled_advisor", "migratedToState": true, "migrationDate": "2026-03-08T18:22:17.408Z", "detectedPredicates": ["proximity.ally-nearby"]}}}
{"_id": "35cd0efb3aae31c7", "name": "Double Agent", "type": "talent", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"prerequisites": "", "benefit": "When you roll Initiative at the beginning of combat, also roll a Deception check, comparing the result to the Will Defense of all enemies in line of sight. If your Deception check is successful, that target cannot attack you and does not believe you to be an enemy (though they do not consider you an ally) while this effect is active.", "description": {"value": "When you roll Initiative at the beginning of combat, also roll a Deception check, comparing the result to the Will Defense of all enemies in line of sight. If your Deception check is successful, that target cannot attack you and does not believe you to be an enemy (though they do not consider you an ally) while this effect is active.\n\nIf you attack or otherwise obviously harm or hinder a target under the effect of this Talent, or one of that target's allies, this effect ends. This is a Mind-Affecting effect."}, "class": "8c58016e587dd2c7", "costNumeric": null, "category": "Noble", "treeId": "4dc70f924e7794ac", "tags": ["action-economy", "defender", "noble", "skills", "social", "support"], "executionModel": "PASSIVE", "subType": "STATE", "abilityMeta": {"modifiers": [{"target": "defense.will", "value": 2, "type": "untyped", "predicates": ["defense.will"], "enabled": true, "priority": 500, "description": "Double Agent"}]}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"swse": {"id": "swse.talent.double_agent", "migratedToState": true, "migrationDate": "2026-03-08T18:22:17.408Z", "detectedPredicates": ["defense.will"]}}}
{"_id": "366ac9dea2e484d3", "name": "Improved Redirect", "type": "talent", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"prerequisites": "Deflect, Redirect Shot", "benefit": "Once per turn, when you successfully Redirect an attack using the Redirect Shot Talent, you do not count the Deflect Talent use that triggered the redirected attack (thus, you take no cumulative penalty to Use the Force checks from that Deflect attempt).", "description": {"value": "Once per turn, when you successfully Redirect an attack using the Redirect Shot Talent, you do not count the Deflect Talent use that triggered the redirected attack (thus, you take no cumulative penalty to Use the Force checks from that Deflect attempt)."}, "class": "fb5c2644f988e6bf", "costNumeric": null, "category": "Jedi Knight", "treeId": "b3c5d90b5036f39b", "tags": ["feat-chain", "jedi", "talent-chain"], "executionModel": "PASSIVE", "subType": "STATE", "abilityMeta": {"modifiers": [{"target": "attack", "value": 0, "type": "untyped", "predicates": [], "enabled": false, "priority": 500, "description": "[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Improved Redirect"}]}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"swse": {"id": "swse.talent.improved_redirect", "migratedToState": true, "migrationDate": "2026-03-08T18:22:17.408Z", "detectedPredicates": []}}}
{"_id": "36f8497081dce05a", "name": "Fast Repairs", "type": "talent", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"prerequisites": "Trained in Mechanics", "benefit": "Whenever you Jury-Rig an object or Vehicle, the Vehicle gains a number of temporary Hit Points equal to the result of your Mechanics check. Damage is subtracted from these temporary Hit Points first, and temporary Hit Points go away at the conclusion of the encounter.", "description": {"value": "Whenever you Jury-Rig an object or Vehicle, the Vehicle gains a number of temporary Hit Points equal to the result of your Mechanics check. Damage is subtracted from these temporary Hit Points first, and temporary Hit Points go away at the conclusion of the encounter."}, "class": "21dfe84d159a1b7f", "costNumeric": null, "category": "Scoundrel", "prerequisitesStructured": {"type": "all", "conditions": [{"type": "skillTrained", "skill": "745a5686d6f21e8c"}], "_source": "fix5F-canonical"}, "treeId": "f1657b1d23a4c7dc", "tags": ["mechanics", "scoundrel", "skills", "striker"], "executionModel": "PASSIVE", "subType": "STATE", "abilityMeta": {"modifiers": [{"target": "skill", "value": 2, "type": "untyped", "predicates": ["attack.when-hit"], "enabled": true, "priority": 500, "description": "Fast Repairs"}]}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"swse": {"id": "swse.talent.fast_repairs", "migratedToState": true, "migrationDate": "2026-03-08T18:22:17.408Z", "detectedPredicates": ["attack.when-hit"]}}}
{"_id": "3713870862584269", "name": "Soothe", "type": "talent", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"prerequisites": "Vital Transfer", "benefit": "When using Vital Transfer to heal somebody, you can move the target +1 step on the Condition Track instead of healing damage. When doing so, you move -1 step on the Condition Track.", "description": {"value": "When using Vital Transfer to heal somebody, you can move the target +1 step on the Condition Track instead of healing damage. When doing so, you move -1 step on the Condition Track."}, "class": "fb5c2644f988e6bf", "costNumeric": null, "category": "Jedi Knight", "treeId": "a2a7a376e4905da9", "tags": ["condition-removal", "controller", "feat-chain", "force", "force-control", "force-support", "jedi", "light-side", "medicine", "mobility", "skills", "striker", "support", "talent-chain"], "executionModel": "PASSIVE", "subType": "STATE", "abilityMeta": {"modifiers": [{"target": "attack", "value": 1, "type": "untyped", "predicates": ["movement.while-moving"], "enabled": true, "priority": 500, "description": "Soothe"}]}}, "effects": [{"_id": "3663846e-dc0d-44d3-ac39-dc181d0f2d63", "name": "Soothe", "icon": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "changes": [{"key": "system.healing", "mode": 2, "value": "1"}], "disabled": false, "duration": {}, "flags": {"swse": {"source": "talent", "talentName": "Soothe"}}}], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"swse": {"id": "swse.talent.soothe", "migratedToState": true, "migrationDate": "2026-03-08T18:22:17.408Z", "detectedPredicates": ["movement.while-moving"]}}}
{"_id": "379019c29b37d717", "name": "Unarmed Parry", "type": "talent", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"prerequisites": "Teräs Käsi Basics, Martial Arts I, Martial Arts II", "benefit": "When you Fight Defensively, as a Reaction you can negate a melee attack by making a successful Unarmed attack roll. If your attack roll equals or exceeds the attack roll of the incoming melee attack, the attack is negated. You must be aware of the attack, and not be Flat-Footed, and you take a cumulative -2 penalty to all attack rolls for each attack roll made since the beginning of your last turn.", "description": {"value": "When you Fight Defensively, as a Reaction you can negate a melee attack by making a successful Unarmed attack roll. If your attack roll equals or exceeds the attack roll of the incoming melee attack, the attack is negated. You must be aware of the attack, and not be Flat-Footed, and you take a cumulative -2 penalty to all attack rolls for each attack roll made since the beginning of your last turn."}, "costNumeric": null, "prerequisitesStructured": {"type": "all", "conditions": [{"type": "talent", "id": "swse.talent.teras_kasi_basics"}], "_source": "canonical-csv"}, "treeId": "ba726f623e42f849", "tags": ["action_economy", "counterattack", "duelist", "martial_arts", "melee", "melee_defense", "offense_melee", "reaction", "tree_ba726f623e42f849", "unarmed", "uncategorized_talent"], "executionModel": "PASSIVE", "subType": "STATE", "abilityMeta": {"modifiers": [{"target": "attack", "value": 2, "type": "untyped", "predicates": ["attack.with-melee"], "enabled": true, "priority": 500, "description": "Unarmed Parry"}]}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"swse": {"id": "swse.talent.unarmed_parry", "migratedToState": true, "migrationDate": "2026-03-08T18:22:17.408Z", "detectedPredicates": ["attack.with-melee"]}}}
{"_id": "37bf53b4b2c0e539", "name": "Wealth", "type": "talent", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"prerequisites": "", "benefit": "Each time you gain a level (including the level at which you select this Talent), you receive an amount of credits equal to 5,000 x your Class Level. You can spend these credits as you see fit.", "description": {"value": "Each time you gain a level (including the level at which you select this Talent), you receive an amount of credits equal to 5,000 x your Class Level. You can spend these credits as you see fit.\n\nThe credits appear in a civilized, accessible location of your choice or in your private bank account."}, "class": "8c58016e587dd2c7", "costNumeric": null, "category": "Noble", "treeId": "b5bb4154688c66ab", "tags": ["noble"], "executionModel": "PASSIVE", "subType": "STATE", "abilityMeta": {"modifiers": [{"target": "attack", "value": 0, "type": "untyped", "predicates": [], "enabled": false, "priority": 500, "description": "[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Wealth"}]}}, "effects": [{"_id": "cd6b58ce-5144-4f39-a76a-720505ecdfc8", "name": "Wealth", "icon": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "changes": [{"key": "system.credits", "mode": 2, "value": "level_per_level"}], "disabled": false, "duration": {}, "flags": {"swse": {"source": "talent", "talentName": "Wealth"}}}], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"swse": {"id": "swse.talent.wealth", "migratedToState": true, "migrationDate": "2026-03-08T18:22:17.408Z", "detectedPredicates": []}}}
{"_id": "37c45caffa191816", "name": "Raider's Frenzy", "type": "talent", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"prerequisites": "", "benefit": "Once per round, when one of your allies within 6 squares successfully damages a target, you grant all your allies within your line of sight a bonus to damage rolls against that target equal to one-half your Class Level until the end of your next turn.", "description": {"value": "Once per round, when one of your allies within 6 squares successfully damages a target, you grant all your allies within your line of sight a bonus to damage rolls against that target equal to one-half your Class Level until the end of your next turn."}, "class": "fcf8cc428a6eb01a", "costNumeric": null, "category": "Master Privateer", "treeId": "61db5e2c0c44ef67", "tags": ["positioning", "scoundrel", "striker", "support", "sustained-damage"], "executionModel": "PASSIVE", "subType": "STATE", "abilityMeta": {"modifiers": [{"target": "attack", "value": 2, "type": "untyped", "predicates": ["turn.once-per-round"], "enabled": true, "priority": 500, "description": "Raider's Frenzy"}]}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"swse": {"id": "swse.talent.raiders_frenzy", "migratedToState": true, "migrationDate": "2026-03-08T18:22:17.408Z", "detectedPredicates": ["turn.once-per-round"]}}}
{"_id": "37ee909a7de54768", "name": "Channel Anger", "type": "talent", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"prerequisites": "Channel Aggression", "benefit": "You let your anger swell into a Rage. As a Swift Action, you may spend a Force Point to gain a +2 Rage bonus on melee attack rolls and melee damage rolls for a number of rounds equal to 5 + your Constitution modifier. At the end of this duration, you move -1 step along the Condition Track.", "description": {"value": "You let your anger swell into a Rage. As a Swift Action, you may spend a Force Point to gain a +2 Rage bonus on melee attack rolls and melee damage rolls for a number of rounds equal to 5 + your Constitution modifier. At the end of this duration, you move -1 step along the Condition Track.\n\nWhile Raging, you cannot use Skills that require patience and concentration, such as Mechanics, Stealth, or Use the Force."}, "class": "289fcf920ef0e184", "costNumeric": null, "category": "Force Adept", "prerequisitesStructured": {"type": "all", "conditions": [{"type": "talent", "id": "swse.talent.channel_aggression"}], "_source": "canonical-csv"}, "treeId": "96ef43a3054dcb58", "tags": ["action_economy", "category_force_adept", "condition_removal", "controller", "dark_side", "feat_chain", "force", "force_capacity", "force_execution", "force_point_spend", "force_training", "melee", "mobility", "mystic", "offense_melee", "resource_spend", "skill_stealth", "stealth", "striker", "sustained_damage", "swift_action", "talent_chain", "tree_96ef43a3054dcb58", "use_the_force"], "executionModel": "PASSIVE", "subType": "STATE", "abilityMeta": {"modifiers": [{"target": "attack", "value": 2, "type": "untyped", "predicates": ["attack.with-melee"], "enabled": true, "priority": 500, "description": "Channel Anger"}]}}, "effects": [{"_id": "c7e68fc9-d1bc-484b-a797-a04a539232fe", "name": "Channel Anger", "icon": "icons/svg/fire.svg", "changes": [{"key": "system.attacks.melee", "mode": 2, "value": "2"}, {"key": "system.damage.melee", "mode": 2, "value": "2"}], "disabled": false, "duration": {}, "flags": {"swse": {"source": "talent", "talentName": "Channel Anger"}}}], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"swse": {"id": "swse.talent.channel_anger", "migratedToState": true, "migrationDate": "2026-03-08T18:22:17.408Z", "detectedPredicates": ["attack.with-melee"]}}}
{"_id": "383915a7d11e1225", "name": "Devastating Attack", "type": "talent", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"prerequisites": "", "benefit": "Choose a single Exotic Weapon or weapon group with which you are proficient. Whenever you make a successful attack against a target using such a weapon, you treat your target's Damage Threshold as if it were 5 points lower when determining the result of your attack. If you select Heavy Weapons as the weapon group this Talent applies to, you may also use the Talent with Vehicle Weapon attacks.", "description": {"value": "Choose a single Exotic Weapon or weapon group with which you are proficient. Whenever you make a successful attack against a target using such a weapon, you treat your target's Damage Threshold as if it were 5 points lower when determining the result of your attack. If you select Heavy Weapons as the weapon group this Talent applies to, you may also use the Talent with Vehicle Weapon attacks.\n\nYou may select this Talent multiple times. Each time you select this Talent, it applies to a different Exotic Weapon or weapon group."}, "class": "f62ca2e639cab614", "costNumeric": null, "category": "Soldier", "treeId": "2f720d8b061f9bd0", "tags": ["soldier"], "executionModel": "PASSIVE", "subType": "STATE", "abilityMeta": {"modifiers": [{"target": "attack", "value": 0, "type": "untyped", "predicates": [], "enabled": false, "priority": 500, "description": "[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Devastating Attack"}]}}, "effects": [{"_id": "69f7a1a0-603e-4b5e-a42a-15f770230266", "name": "Devastating Attack", "icon": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "changes": [{"key": "system.combat.weaponGroupThresholdReduction", "mode": 2, "value": "5"}], "disabled": false, "duration": {}, "flags": {"swse": {"source": "talent", "talentName": "Devastating Attack", "effectType": "threshold_reduction", "weaponGroupSpecific": true, "notes": "Weapon group specific - applies when using designated weapon group"}}}], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"swse": {"id": "swse.talent.devastating_attack", "migratedToState": true, "migrationDate": "2026-03-08T18:22:17.408Z", "detectedPredicates": []}}}
{"_id": "388f30468a80f221", "name": "Synchronized Fire", "type": "talent", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"prerequisites": "Expert Gunner", "benefit": "Once per encounter, you may ready to fire a single weapon at the same target as an ally, and you coordinate with a single weapon of your ally.", "description": {"value": "Once per encounter, you may ready to fire a single weapon at the same target as an ally, and you coordinate with a single weapon of your ally.\n\nIf both attacks hit, you add the damage of the two weapons together before applying the target's Shield Rating or Damage Reduction, and treat it as a single attack for purposes of exceeding the target's Damage Threshold."}, "class": "9c9989c34714f920", "costNumeric": null, "category": "Ace Pilot", "prerequisitesStructured": {"type": "all", "conditions": [{"type": "talent", "id": "swse.talent.expert_gunner"}], "_source": "canonical-csv"}, "treeId": "43ead399d82b8142", "tags": ["feat-chain", "scout", "support", "talent-chain"], "executionModel": "PASSIVE", "subType": "STATE", "abilityMeta": {"modifiers": [{"target": "attack", "value": 2, "type": "untyped", "predicates": ["turn.once-per-round"], "enabled": true, "priority": 500, "description": "Synchronized Fire"}]}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"swse": {"id": "swse.talent.synchronized_fire", "migratedToState": true, "migrationDate": "2026-03-08T18:22:17.408Z", "detectedPredicates": ["turn.once-per-round"]}}}
{"_id": "38e64db2b516759a", "name": "Renowned Pilot", "type": "talent", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"prerequisites": "", "benefit": "Your reputation as a skilled pilot precedes you and bolsters the resolve of your allies. All allies within 6 squares of a Vehicle you Pilot can reroll one Pilot check, keeping the better of the two results.", "description": {"value": "Your reputation as a skilled pilot precedes you and bolsters the resolve of your allies. All allies within 6 squares of a Vehicle you Pilot can reroll one Pilot check, keeping the better of the two results.\n\nOnce an ally has used this ability, that same ally cannot gain this Talent's benefit during the same encounter."}, "class": "9c9989c34714f920", "costNumeric": null, "category": "Ace Pilot", "treeId": "b17c1515c06361d6", "tags": ["positioning", "scout", "support"], "executionModel": "PASSIVE", "subType": "STATE", "abilityMeta": {"modifiers": [{"target": "skill", "value": 2, "type": "untyped", "predicates": ["proximity.ally-nearby", "proximity.count-allies-within-12"], "enabled": true, "priority": 500, "description": "Renowned Pilot"}]}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"swse": {"id": "swse.talent.renowned_pilot", "migratedToState": true, "migrationDate": "2026-03-08T18:22:17.408Z", "detectedPredicates": ["proximity.ally-nearby", "proximity.count-allies-within-12"]}}}
{"_id": "394809ed8baff1b9", "name": "Improved Armored Defense", "type": "talent", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"prerequisites": "Armored Defense", "benefit": "When calculating your Reflex Defense, you may add your Heroic Level plus one-half your Armor bonus (rounded down), or your Armor bonus, whichever is higher. You must be proficient with the Armor you are wearing to gain this benefit.", "description": {"value": "When calculating your Reflex Defense, you may add your Heroic Level plus one-half your Armor bonus (rounded down), or your Armor bonus, whichever is higher. You must be proficient with the Armor you are wearing to gain this benefit."}, "class": "f62ca2e639cab614", "costNumeric": null, "category": "Soldier", "prerequisitesStructured": {"type": "all", "conditions": [{"type": "talent", "id": "swse.talent.armored_defense"}], "_source": "canonical-csv"}, "treeId": "17cec542331cb4e4", "tags": ["armor", "defender", "feat-chain", "soldier", "striker", "talent-chain"], "executionModel": "PASSIVE", "subType": "MODIFIER", "abilityMeta": {"modifiers": [{"target": "defense.reflex", "type": "untyped", "value": 2, "enabled": true, "priority": 500, "description": "Migrated from AE system.defenses.reflex"}]}}, "effects": [{"_id": "842ee02b-8f7e-4a40-802a-c6fe553379a5", "name": "Improved Armored Defense", "icon": "icons/svg/shield.svg", "changes": [{"key": "system.defenses.reflex", "mode": 2, "value": "2"}], "disabled": true, "duration": {}, "flags": {"swse": {"source": "talent", "talentName": "Improved Armored Defense", "migratedToPassive": true}}}], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"swse": {"id": "swse.talent.improved_armored_defense"}}}
{"_id": "395daa7cd6f14b8f", "name": "Rough Landings", "type": "talent", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"prerequisites": "Emergency Maneuvers, BAB +6", "description": "- You automatically succeed on your piloting check to land while Sputtering or moving Full-Throttle. Also, if you’re conscious when landing with a deployed Emergency Chute, you take no damage from falling and aren’t knocked prone. Once per round, if something Grabs you and you have 6 squares of vertical space above you, then as an immediate reaction (including before any Grapple Checks), you can burn 3 charges to instantly escape the grab, ending your movement 6 squares up. Beings with Intelligence 2 or more can choose to try to maintain their grab: as a Swift Action, they can make a second Grab Check. If the weight of your equipment + your target + their equipment doesn’t exceed twice your Carrying Capacity, you drag them with you 6 squares up (they can use a free action to let go at any point in this ascent). However, if the weight exceeds twice your carrying capacity, you remain grabbed and stationary. If you're airborne and still grabbed, you can't automatically escape the grab on your turn. You must succeed on a contested grapple check. If you win, the grab ends and they either fall or activate their own fly speed as a reaction. If they win, the grab is maintained. Neither side may use grapple maneuvers (e.g., Trip, Pin). You can Activate your jet pack with a free action on your turn or at the start of a Surprise Round if you’re not surprised. If you have your Jumptrooper Qualification, you can also activate Full-Throttle Mode in the same turn that you Activate your jet pack. Refer to the talent of the same name from the Rocket Jumper Talent Tree, but the speed bonus applies only when in Hover and Sweep Mode. Refer to the talent of the same name from the Rocket Jumper Talent Tree. Like a carrion crow, you can grab your prey, gain altitude, and drop them to the ground. Once per encounter, if you still have your three actions available (Swift, Standard, Move) on your current turn and 12 squares of vertical space above you, then as a standard action, you can attempt a Grab per normal rules except that you don’t provoke an Attack of Opportunity and your attack penalty is only -2. If you succeed, as long as the weight of your equipment + your target + their equipment doesn’t exceed twice your Carrying Capacity, you immediately spend your move action to burn 4 charges and drag your target 12 squares straight up, then spend your swift action to release the target in a square next to you - these follow up actions can’t be delayed. You cause 2d6 bludgeoning damage from the rough handling. Instead of a grab, you can ranged grab with appropriate equipment (e.g., Snare Pistol, Whipcord, Shock Whip), but the target must be within 2 squares range. Your released target doesn’t fall to the ground until the beginning of your next turn, giving them and their allies a chance to prevent the worst outcome. (E.g., they could activate their own fly speed on their turn.) Otherwise, the GM determines the target’s Falling Damage for 18 meters at the beginning of your turn using normal rules. Full-Throttle Mode no longer applies a -2 attack penalty. When you’re in All-Out Movement Mode, as a free action once per turn, you may make one ranged attack with a pistol, rifle, or jet pack integrated missile launcher. This attack has a -2 penalty.", "benefit": "- You automatically succeed on your piloting check to land while Sputtering or moving Full-Throttle. Also, if you’re conscious when landing with a deployed Emergency Chute, you take no damage from falling and aren’t knocked prone. Once per round, if something Grabs you and you have 6 squares of vertical space above you, then as an immediate reaction (including before any Grapple Checks), you can burn 3 charges to instantly escape the grab, ending your movement 6 squares up. Beings with Intelligence 2 or more can choose to try to maintain their grab: as a Swift Action, they can make a second Grab Check. If the weight of your equipment + your target + their equipment doesn’t exceed twice your Carrying Capacity, you drag them with you 6 squares up (they can use a free action to let go at any point in this ascent). However, if the weight exceeds twice your carrying capacity, you remain grabbed and stationary. If you're airborne and still grabbed, you can't automatically escape the grab on your turn. You must succeed on a contested grapple check. If you win, the grab ends and they either fall or activate their own fly speed as a reaction. If they win, the grab is maintained. Neither side may use grapple maneuvers (e.g., Trip, Pin). You can Activate your jet pack with a free action on your turn or at the start of a Surprise Round if you’re not surprised. If you have your Jumptrooper Qualification, you can also activate Full-Throttle Mode in the same turn that you Activate your jet pack. Refer to the talent of the same name from the Rocket Jumper Talent Tree, but the speed bonus applies only when in Hover and Sweep Mode. Refer to the talent of the same name from the Rocket Jumper Talent Tree. Like a carrion crow, you can grab your prey, gain altitude, and drop them to the ground. Once per encounter, if you still have your three actions available (Swift, Standard, Move) on your current turn and 12 squares of vertical space above you, then as a standard action, you can attempt a Grab per normal rules except that you don’t provoke an Attack of Opportunity and your attack penalty is only -2. If you succeed, as long as the weight of your equipment + your target + their equipment doesn’t exceed twice your Carrying Capacity, you immediately spend your move action to burn 4 charges and drag your target 12 squares straight up, then spend your swift action to release the target in a square next to you - these follow up actions can’t be delayed. You cause 2d6 bludgeoning damage from the rough handling. Instead of a grab, you can ranged grab with appropriate equipment (e.g., Snare Pistol, Whipcord, Shock Whip), but the target must be within 2 squares range. Your released target doesn’t fall to the ground until the beginning of your next turn, giving them and their allies a chance to prevent the worst outcome. (E.g., they could activate their own fly speed on their turn.) Otherwise, the GM determines the target’s Falling Damage for 18 meters at the beginning of your turn using normal rules. Full-Throttle Mode no longer applies a -2 attack penalty. When you’re in All-Out Movement Mode, as a free action once per turn, you may make one ranged attack with a pistol, rifle, or jet pack integrated missile launcher. This attack has a -2 penalty.", "class": "", "category": "", "costNumeric": null, "treeId": "25d99948c9cb41ad", "tags": ["action_economy", "ambush", "control", "controller", "feat_chain", "heavy_weapons", "mobility", "move_action", "new_action", "offense_ranged", "pilot", "piloting", "positioning", "ranged", "reaction", "skills", "standard_action", "striker", "support", "survivability", "sustained_damage", "swift_action", "talent_chain", "trap", "tree_25d99948c9cb41ad", "uncategorized_talent", "vehicle"], "executionModel": "PASSIVE", "subType": "STATE", "abilityMeta": {"modifiers": [{"target": "skill", "value": 2, "type": "untyped", "predicates": ["attack.with-ranged", "turn.on-current-turn", "turn.once-per-round", "target.is-prone"], "enabled": true, "priority": 500, "description": "Rough Landings"}]}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"swse": {"migratedToState": true, "migrationDate": "2026-03-08T18:22:17.408Z", "detectedPredicates": ["attack.with-ranged", "turn.on-current-turn", "turn.once-per-round", "target.is-prone"]}}}
