{"_id": "616bc0afc5c847ea", "name": "Get Down", "type": "talent", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"prerequisites": "", "description": {"value": "As a Reaction, when an ally is targeted by a ranged attack, you can enable that ally to drop Prone immediately (imposing the normal -5 penalty for a ranged attack against a Prone target to the triggering attack roll) as a Free Action."}, "benefit": "As a Reaction, when an ally is targeted by a ranged attack, you can enable that ally to drop Prone immediately (imposing the normal -5 penalty for a ranged attack against a Prone target to the triggering attack roll) as a Free Action.", "class": "", "category": "", "costNumeric": null, "treeId": "3a785c985eae4d00", "tags": ["action_economy", "ally_support", "ambush_defense", "controller", "mobility", "offense_ranged", "positioning", "reaction", "support", "sustained_damage", "tree_3a785c985eae4d00", "uncategorized_talent"], "executionModel": "PASSIVE", "subType": "STATE", "abilityMeta": {"modifiers": [{"target": "attack", "value": 2, "type": "untyped", "predicates": ["proximity.ally-nearby", "turn.once-per-round"], "enabled": true, "priority": 500, "description": "Get Down"}]}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"swse": {"migratedToState": true, "migrationDate": "2026-03-08T18:22:17.414Z", "detectedPredicates": ["proximity.ally-nearby", "turn.once-per-round"]}}}
{"_id": "618472c99f355949", "name": "Long Stride", "type": "talent", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"prerequisites": "", "benefit": "Your Speed increases by 2 squares if you are wearing Light Armor or no Armor. If you have a natural Fly, Climb, or Swim Speed, it increases by 2 squares as well.", "description": {"value": "Your Speed increases by 2 squares if you are wearing Light Armor or no Armor. If you have a natural Fly, Climb, or Swim Speed, it increases by 2 squares as well.\n\nYou cannot use this Talent if you are wearing Medium Armor or Heavy Armor."}, "class": "b5bed5d1b5f42958", "costNumeric": null, "category": "Scout", "treeId": "dca33c0215264a02", "tags": ["action-economy", "ambush", "controller", "feat-chain", "mobility", "scout", "striker", "support", "sustained-damage", "talent-chain"], "executionModel": "PASSIVE", "subType": "MODIFIER", "abilityMeta": {"modifiers": [{"target": "speed.base", "type": "untyped", "value": 2, "enabled": true, "priority": 500, "description": "Migrated from AE system.speed"}]}}, "effects": [{"_id": "1379eb45-3cb6-42c3-aabe-c8747b8d5bf0", "name": "Long Stride", "icon": "icons/svg/running.svg", "changes": [{"key": "system.speed", "mode": 2, "value": "2", "priority": 20}], "disabled": true, "duration": {}, "flags": {"swse": {"source": "talent", "talentName": "Long Stride", "migratedToPassive": true}}}], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"swse": {"id": "swse.talent.long_stride"}}}
{"_id": "61c9413bde23411a", "name": "Extended Sputters", "type": "talent", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"prerequisites": "", "description": "- You’ve learned a few throttle tricks that can extend the duration of your jet pack’s Sputtering state from one turn to two consecutive turns. However, if you use these tricks, you can’t use any move actions to gain altitude during this sputter.", "benefit": "- You’ve learned a few throttle tricks that can extend the duration of your jet pack’s Sputtering state from one turn to two consecutive turns. However, if you use these tricks, you can’t use any move actions to gain altitude during this sputter.", "class": "", "category": "", "costNumeric": null, "treeId": "25d99948c9cb41ad", "tags": ["action_economy", "controller", "mobility", "pilot", "survivability", "tree_25d99948c9cb41ad", "uncategorized_talent", "vehicle"], "executionModel": "PASSIVE", "subType": "STATE", "abilityMeta": {"modifiers": [{"target": "attack", "value": 0, "type": "untyped", "predicates": [], "enabled": false, "priority": 500, "description": "[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Extended Sputters"}]}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"swse": {"migratedToState": true, "migrationDate": "2026-03-08T18:22:17.414Z", "detectedPredicates": []}}}
{"_id": "627bd3abd30b973f", "name": "Power of the Dark Side", "type": "talent", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"prerequisites": "Dark Side Score equal to Wisdom Score", "benefit": "Charisma 13 As a Standard Action, you grant yourself and all allies within 6 squares of you a +1 Force bonus to all Defenses until the end of the encounter. These bonuses are lost if you fall unconscious or die. Affected allies that move out of range lose the benefits for as long as they remain out of range. Prerequisite: Once per day, you can use a Force Power that normally takes a Standard Action or a Move Action as a Swift Action. Reference Book: Star Wars Saga Edition Clone Wars Campaign Guide Sometimes your anger consumes you. As a Swift Action, you can take a -5 penalty to your Will Defense to gain a +2 Force bonus on attack rolls. The penalty and bonus last until the beginning of your next turn. Reference Book: Star Wars Saga Edition Legacy Era Campaign Guide Prerequisite: Whenever an effect would normally move you down the Condition Track, you may spend a Force Point and increase your Dark Side Score by 1 to negate that movement down the Condition Track. Reference Book: Star Wars Saga Edition Jedi Academy Training Manual Once per encounter as a Swift Action, you can return one Force Power with the [Dark Side] descriptor to your Force Power Suite without spending a Force Point. You can select this Talent multiple times. Each time you select it, you can use it one additional time per encounter. Reference Book: Star Wars Saga Edition Threats of the Galaxy As a Standard Action, you can spend a Force Point to drain the knowledge of an opponent you touch; you must succeed on a Use the Force check (DC equal to the target's Will Defense) to activate this Talent, and if you fail to activate this Talent, you may not try again on the same target for one day. If successful, you immediately become Trained in one Skill that the target is Trained in; if you are already Trained in that Skill, you instead gain Skill Focus in that Skill. This effect lasts for one day. Additionally, your target moves -1 Persistent step along the Condition Track, and the Persistent Condition can be removed only by resting for 8 hours. Additionally, you can choose to instead sift through the mind of the target, looking for a specific piece of knowledge or information. Doing so requires you to make a Perception check against the target's Will Defense; success indicates that you pull the relevant information from the target's mind. When you do so, you do not gain the bonus Trained Skill or Skill Focus normally granted by this Talent, but otherwise the Talent functions as normal. Using this Talent increases your Dark Side Score by 1. Reference Book: Star Wars Saga Edition Jedi Academy Training Manual When you die, you become a Dark Side Spirit until the end of the encounter. You continue to occupy a space in this form, but other creatures can occupy the same space or move through your space without impediment. As a Standard Action, you can attempt to possess an adjacent target. You must succeed on a Use the Force check against an adjacent target's Will Defense. If your check result equals or exceeds the target's Will Defense, you deal 8d6 points of Stun damage to the target; if you reduce the target to 0 Hit Points or move it to the bottom of the Condition Track with this attack, you possess the target as though it were a willing host. Alternatively, as a Standard Action, you can transfer your essence into a single adjacent object, such as a Holocron or a Lightsaber. If you do so, you lie dormant within the object until another creature attempts to use that object, at which time you can emerge and attempt to possess the creature, as described above. If you do not possess a creature or object within 10 rounds of manifesting as a Dark Side Spirit, your spirit dissipates and ceases to exist. Reference Book: Star Wars Saga Edition Force Unleashed Campaign Guide Prerequisite: When you roll a Natural 20 on a Use the Force check to activate a Force Power that directly deals damage to a target, you can choose not to regain all of your spent Force Powers as normal and instead the targets damaged by the Force Power take half that damage again at the start of their next turn. Only Force Powers that directly damage the target are subject to this Talent, including Corruption, Force Blast, Force Grip, Force Lightning, Force Slam, Force Thrust (only when spending a Force Point), and Repulse (only when spending a Force Point). Homebrew Reference Book: Legacy of the Force Sourcebook Prerequisite: You can create balls of unnatural energy, enabling you to make a ranged attack roll against the Reflex Defense of one target within 12 squares and line of sight, dealing 2d6 points of energy damage to the target on a successful attack. Using this Talent increases your Dark Side Score by 1. Homebrew Reference Book: Legacy of the Force Sourcebook Prerequisites: , Swift Power When using a Force Power that directly inflicts damage, you treat the target's Damage Threshold as though it were 5 points lower when determining if the target moves along the Condition Track. Homebrew Reference Book: Legacy of the Force Sourcebook Prerequisite: Whenever your character moves 3 or more squares in a round you gain Concealment; you may choose not to use this Talent when you move.", "description": "Charisma 13 As a Standard Action, you grant yourself and all allies within 6 squares of you a +1 Force bonus to all Defenses until the end of the encounter. These bonuses are lost if you fall unconscious or die. Affected allies that move out of range lose the benefits for as long as they remain out of range. Prerequisite: Once per day, you can use a Force Power that normally takes a Standard Action or a Move Action as a Swift Action. Reference Book: Star Wars Saga Edition Clone Wars Campaign Guide Sometimes your anger consumes you. As a Swift Action, you can take a -5 penalty to your Will Defense to gain a +2 Force bonus on attack rolls. The penalty and bonus last until the beginning of your next turn. Reference Book: Star Wars Saga Edition Legacy Era Campaign Guide Prerequisite: Whenever an effect would normally move you down the Condition Track, you may spend a Force Point and increase your Dark Side Score by 1 to negate that movement down the Condition Track. Reference Book: Star Wars Saga Edition Jedi Academy Training Manual Once per encounter as a Swift Action, you can return one Force Power with the [Dark Side] descriptor to your Force Power Suite without spending a Force Point. You can select this Talent multiple times. Each time you select it, you can use it one additional time per encounter. Reference Book: Star Wars Saga Edition Threats of the Galaxy As a Standard Action, you can spend a Force Point to drain the knowledge of an opponent you touch; you must succeed on a Use the Force check (DC equal to the target's Will Defense) to activate this Talent, and if you fail to activate this Talent, you may not try again on the same target for one day. If successful, you immediately become Trained in one Skill that the target is Trained in; if you are already Trained in that Skill, you instead gain Skill Focus in that Skill. This effect lasts for one day. Additionally, your target moves -1 Persistent step along the Condition Track, and the Persistent Condition can be removed only by resting for 8 hours. Additionally, you can choose to instead sift through the mind of the target, looking for a specific piece of knowledge or information. Doing so requires you to make a Perception check against the target's Will Defense; success indicates that you pull the relevant information from the target's mind. When you do so, you do not gain the bonus Trained Skill or Skill Focus normally granted by this Talent, but otherwise the Talent functions as normal. Using this Talent increases your Dark Side Score by 1. Reference Book: Star Wars Saga Edition Jedi Academy Training Manual When you die, you become a Dark Side Spirit until the end of the encounter. You continue to occupy a space in this form, but other creatures can occupy the same space or move through your space without impediment. As a Standard Action, you can attempt to possess an adjacent target. You must succeed on a Use the Force check against an adjacent target's Will Defense. If your check result equals or exceeds the target's Will Defense, you deal 8d6 points of Stun damage to the target; if you reduce the target to 0 Hit Points or move it to the bottom of the Condition Track with this attack, you possess the target as though it were a willing host. Alternatively, as a Standard Action, you can transfer your essence into a single adjacent object, such as a Holocron or a Lightsaber. If you do so, you lie dormant within the object until another creature attempts to use that object, at which time you can emerge and attempt to possess the creature, as described above. If you do not possess a creature or object within 10 rounds of manifesting as a Dark Side Spirit, your spirit dissipates and ceases to exist. Reference Book: Star Wars Saga Edition Force Unleashed Campaign Guide Prerequisite: When you roll a Natural 20 on a Use the Force check to activate a Force Power that directly deals damage to a target, you can choose not to regain all of your spent Force Powers as normal and instead the targets damaged by the Force Power take half that damage again at the start of their next turn. Only Force Powers that directly damage the target are subject to this Talent, including Corruption, Force Blast, Force Grip, Force Lightning, Force Slam, Force Thrust (only when spending a Force Point), and Repulse (only when spending a Force Point). Homebrew Reference Book: Legacy of the Force Sourcebook Prerequisite: You can create balls of unnatural energy, enabling you to make a ranged attack roll against the Reflex Defense of one target within 12 squares and line of sight, dealing 2d6 points of energy damage to the target on a successful attack. Using this Talent increases your Dark Side Score by 1. Homebrew Reference Book: Legacy of the Force Sourcebook Prerequisites: , Swift Power When using a Force Power that directly inflicts damage, you treat the target's Damage Threshold as though it were 5 points lower when determining if the target moves along the Condition Track. Homebrew Reference Book: Legacy of the Force Sourcebook Prerequisite: Whenever your character moves 3 or more squares in a round you gain Concealment; you may choose not to use this Talent when you move.", "costNumeric": null, "treeId": "de95d37c72b1c4cd", "tags": ["action_economy", "condition_removal", "controller", "damage_reduction", "dark_side", "dark_side_mastery", "defender", "feat_chain", "force", "force_capacity", "force_control", "force_defense", "force_execution", "force_multiplier", "force_offense", "force_point_spend", "force_power_synergy", "forecast_value", "investigation", "knowledge", "leader", "light_side", "lightsaber", "melee", "mobility", "move_action", "new_action", "offense_melee", "offense_ranged", "perception", "positioning", "ranged", "resource_spend", "scaling", "skills", "standard_action", "stealth", "striker", "support", "sustained_damage", "swift_action", "talent_chain", "tree_de95d37c72b1c4cd", "uncategorized_talent", "use_the_force"], "executionModel": "PASSIVE", "subType": "MODIFIER", "abilityMeta": {"modifiers": [{"target": "damage", "type": "untyped", "value": 1, "enabled": true, "priority": 500, "description": "Migrated from AE system.damage"}]}}, "effects": [{"_id": "b3ad7fe2-78a8-42b3-83dc-385122d061ed", "name": "Power of the Dark Side", "icon": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "changes": [{"key": "system.damage", "mode": 2, "value": "1"}], "disabled": true, "duration": {}, "flags": {"swse": {"source": "talent", "talentName": "Power of the Dark Side", "migratedToPassive": true}}}], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"swse": {"id": "swse.talent.power_of_the_dark_side"}}}
{"_id": "629a0efa292511b7", "name": "Trakata", "type": "talent", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"prerequisites": "Weapon Focus (Lightsabers), Weapon Specialization (Lightsabers), Base Attack Bonus +12", "benefit": "By harnessing the unique characteristics of a Lightsaber, you can catch your opponent off guard by quickly shutting off and reigniting the blade. When wielding a Lightsaber, you may spend two Swift Actions to make a Deception check to Feint in combat.", "description": {"value": "By harnessing the unique characteristics of a Lightsaber, you can catch your opponent off guard by quickly shutting off and reigniting the blade. When wielding a Lightsaber, you may spend two Swift Actions to make a Deception check to Feint in combat."}, "class": "fb5c2644f988e6bf", "costNumeric": null, "category": "Jedi Knight", "treeId": "2bc2572e852832e4", "tags": ["action-economy", "feat-chain", "jedi", "lightsaber", "melee", "skills", "social", "talent-chain"], "executionModel": "PASSIVE", "subType": "STATE", "abilityMeta": {"modifiers": [{"target": "attack", "value": 0, "type": "untyped", "predicates": [], "enabled": false, "priority": 500, "description": "[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Trakata"}]}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"swse": {"id": "swse.talent.trakata", "migratedToState": true, "migrationDate": "2026-03-08T18:22:17.414Z", "detectedPredicates": []}}}
{"_id": "62d461ae3b0fcfa9", "name": "Move Massive Object", "type": "talent", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"prerequisites": "Telekinetic Power", "benefit": "Use Move Object to make an area attack (sizes: Large 2x2, Huge 3x3, Gargantuan 4x4, Colossal 6x6); compare Use the Force to Reflex Defense.", "description": "Use Move Object to create an area attack based on object size.", "costNumeric": null, "prerequisitesStructured": {"type": "all", "conditions": [{"type": "talent", "id": "swse.talent.telekinetic_power"}], "_source": "canonical-csv"}, "treeId": "6ac3416fb6aada56", "tags": ["battlefield_control", "controller", "defender", "feat_chain", "force", "force_control", "force_defense", "force_execution", "force_offense", "mobility", "skill_substitution", "talent_chain", "telekinesis", "telepathy", "tree_6ac3416fb6aada56", "uncategorized_talent", "use_the_force"], "executionModel": "PASSIVE", "subType": "STATE", "abilityMeta": {"modifiers": [{"target": "defense.reflex", "value": 2, "type": "untyped", "predicates": ["defense.reflex"], "enabled": true, "priority": 500, "description": "Move Massive Object"}]}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"swse": {"id": "swse.talent.move_massive_object", "migratedToState": true, "migrationDate": "2026-03-08T18:22:17.414Z", "detectedPredicates": ["defense.reflex"]}}}
{"_id": "62d47b8982b6591e", "name": "Powerful Friends", "type": "talent", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"prerequisites": "Connections, Influential Friends", "benefit": "You have a powerful contact who has an extended sphere of influence. The contact could be an Imperial Senator, a high-level military officer, a regional governor, an infamous crime lord, or another person of similar significance.", "description": {"value": "You have a powerful contact who has an extended sphere of influence. The contact could be an Imperial Senator, a high-level military officer, a regional governor, an infamous crime lord, or another person of similar significance.\n\nOnce per encounter, you can invoke the name or office of your powerful contact and Take 20 on one Persuasion check, with no increase in the time needed to make the check."}, "class": "8c58016e587dd2c7", "costNumeric": null, "category": "Noble", "prerequisitesStructured": {"type": "all", "conditions": [{"type": "talent", "id": "swse.talent.influential_friends"}], "_source": "canonical-csv"}, "treeId": "b5bb4154688c66ab", "tags": ["feat-chain", "noble", "skills", "social", "talent-chain"], "executionModel": "PASSIVE", "subType": "STATE", "abilityMeta": {"modifiers": [{"target": "skill", "value": 2, "type": "untyped", "predicates": ["turn.once-per-round"], "enabled": true, "priority": 500, "description": "Powerful Friends"}]}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"swse": {"id": "swse.talent.powerful_friends", "migratedToState": true, "migrationDate": "2026-03-08T18:22:17.414Z", "detectedPredicates": ["turn.once-per-round"]}}}
{"_id": "62e70280d08f43ec", "name": "Allure", "type": "talent", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"prerequisites": "", "description": "As a Full-Round Action, you can beguile one or more targets of your choice within 6 squares and line of sight, making a Persuasion check against their Will Defense. If successful, the targets suffer a -5 penalty to Perception checks for one round. You can keep the targets captivated as a Full-Round Action each subsequent round, making a new Persuasion check each time. The effect immediately ends if the targets are attacked or threatened. Homebrew Reference Book: New Republic Campaign Guide When making an opposed Deception or Persuasion check, you receive a +2 circumstance bonus to the check. Additionally, in the case of a tie in the opposed check, your result is victorious. If your opponent also has this Talent, normal resolution rules apply. Homebrew Reference Book: New Republic Campaign Guide You receive a +2 competence bonus to all Deception and Persuasion checks. Additionally, you are also considered Trained in those skill if not already.", "benefit": "As a Full-Round Action, you can beguile one or more targets of your choice within 6 squares and line of sight, making a Persuasion check against their Will Defense. If successful, the targets suffer a -5 penalty to Perception checks for one round. You can keep the targets captivated as a Full-Round Action each subsequent round, making a new Persuasion check each time. The effect immediately ends if the targets are attacked or threatened. Homebrew Reference Book: New Republic Campaign Guide When making an opposed Deception or Persuasion check, you receive a +2 circumstance bonus to the check. Additionally, in the case of a tie in the opposed check, your result is victorious. If your opponent also has this Talent, normal resolution rules apply. Homebrew Reference Book: New Republic Campaign Guide You receive a +2 competence bonus to all Deception and Persuasion checks. Additionally, you are also considered Trained in those skill if not already.", "class": "", "category": "", "costNumeric": null, "treeId": "8375b9b26b679901", "tags": ["action_economy", "charm", "deception", "defender", "mind_affecting", "perception", "persuasion", "positioning", "skills", "social", "social_control", "striker", "support", "sustained_damage", "tree_8375b9b26b679901", "uncategorized_talent"], "executionModel": "PASSIVE", "subType": "STATE", "abilityMeta": {"modifiers": [{"target": "defense.will", "value": 2, "type": "untyped", "predicates": ["defense.will", "proximity.ally-nearby"], "enabled": true, "priority": 500, "description": "Allure"}]}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"swse": {"migratedToState": true, "migrationDate": "2026-03-08T18:22:17.414Z", "detectedPredicates": ["defense.will", "proximity.ally-nearby"]}}}
