{"_id": "856812052aa6c6d2", "name": "Vehicular Boost", "type": "talent", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"prerequisites": "", "benefit": "As a Standard Action, you can make a DC 15 Mechanics check to grant one Vehicle you occupy a number of Bonus Hit Points equal to 5 x your Class Level. Damage is subtracted from the Bonus Hit Points first, and any Bonus Hit Points remaining at the end of the encounter go away. Bonus Hit Points from multiple sources do not stack.", "description": {"value": "As a Standard Action, you can make a DC 15 Mechanics check to grant one Vehicle you occupy a number of Bonus Hit Points equal to 5 x your Class Level. Damage is subtracted from the Bonus Hit Points first, and any Bonus Hit Points remaining at the end of the encounter go away. Bonus Hit Points from multiple sources do not stack."}, "class": "b85240cf77cf95eb", "costNumeric": null, "category": "Military Engineer", "treeId": "e32009b1b0aee8c9", "tags": ["mechanics", "skills", "striker"], "executionModel": "PASSIVE", "subType": "STATE", "abilityMeta": {"modifiers": [{"target": "attack", "value": 0, "type": "untyped", "predicates": [], "enabled": false, "priority": 500, "description": "[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Vehicular Boost"}]}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"swse": {"id": "swse.talent.vehicular_boost", "migratedToState": true, "migrationDate": "2026-03-08T18:22:17.420Z", "detectedPredicates": []}}}
{"_id": "85e348f24a144e1c", "name": "Inspired", "type": "talent", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"prerequisites": "", "description": "As a Standard Action, you can inspire confidence in all allies in your line of sight, granting them a +1 morale bonus on attack rolls, and a +1 morale bonus on Skill Checks for the rest of the encounter, or until you're unconscious or dead. Once , your allies don't need to remain within line of sight of you.", "benefit": "As a Standard Action, you can inspire confidence in all allies in your line of sight, granting them a +1 morale bonus on attack rolls, and a +1 morale bonus on Skill Checks for the rest of the encounter, or until you're unconscious or dead. Once , your allies don't need to remain within line of sight of you.", "class": "", "category": "", "costNumeric": null, "treeId": "72d32ebcbb607314", "tags": ["action_economy", "ally_support", "leader", "morale", "new_action", "standard_action", "striker", "tree_72d32ebcbb607314", "uncategorized_talent"], "executionModel": "PASSIVE", "subType": "STATE", "abilityMeta": {"modifiers": [{"target": "attack", "value": 0, "type": "untyped", "predicates": [], "enabled": false, "priority": 500, "description": "[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Inspired"}]}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"swse": {"migratedToState": true, "migrationDate": "2026-03-08T18:22:17.420Z", "detectedPredicates": []}}}
{"_id": "85e9699cee664641", "name": "Identify Creature", "type": "talent", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"prerequisites": "Trained in Use Computer", "description": "As a Standard Action, you can make a Knowledge (Life Sciences) check against a DC of 10 + the CL of a single non-Droid creature. If successful, you grant all allies that can hear and understand you a bonus to their attack rolls against that creature. This bonus is equal to your Intelligence modifier (minimum +1), and lasts until the beginning of your next turn. Choose a single Knowledge Field (Bureaucracy, Galactic Lore, Life Sciences, Physical Sciences, Social Sciences, Tactics, or Technology). If you fail a Knowledge check with that Knowledge Field, you can spend a Full-Round Action as long as you have access to a computer network to reroll the check. You use your Use Computer skill in lieu of your Knowledge skill, and keep the better of the two results. You may select this Talent multiple times. Each time you select this Talent, it applies to a different Knowledge Field. You use your experience in xenobiology to recall a creature's traits and abilities. As a Swift Action, you can select a single non-Droid creature within line of sight and make a Knowledge (Life Sciences) check against a DC equal to 15 + the creature's CL. If the check is successful, you immediately learn any two (your choice) of the following pieces of information: Creature's Base Attack Bonus or attack bonus with a particular attack Any one of the creature's Defense Scores Any one of the creature's Skill modifier The presence of any one special quality or Feat (you choose the special quality or Feat, and the Gamemaster reveals whether or not it is present) You can make a Treat Injury check in place of a Mechanics check to Build Object to create a variety of Poisons, using your knowledge of specialized chemicals. When using this Talent, the Hit Point modifier for crafting is equal to the Poison's Challenge Level (for example, Knockout Drugs (CL 2) have a Hit Point modifier of x2). One dose of Poison is equal in size to a Fine object. The complexity of a Poison is determined by its Challenge Level (CL):", "benefit": "As a Standard Action, you can make a Knowledge (Life Sciences) check against a DC of 10 + the CL of a single non-Droid creature. If successful, you grant all allies that can hear and understand you a bonus to their attack rolls against that creature. This bonus is equal to your Intelligence modifier (minimum +1), and lasts until the beginning of your next turn. Choose a single Knowledge Field (Bureaucracy, Galactic Lore, Life Sciences, Physical Sciences, Social Sciences, Tactics, or Technology). If you fail a Knowledge check with that Knowledge Field, you can spend a Full-Round Action as long as you have access to a computer network to reroll the check. You use your Use Computer skill in lieu of your Knowledge skill, and keep the better of the two results. You may select this Talent multiple times. Each time you select this Talent, it applies to a different Knowledge Field. You use your experience in xenobiology to recall a creature's traits and abilities. As a Swift Action, you can select a single non-Droid creature within line of sight and make a Knowledge (Life Sciences) check against a DC equal to 15 + the creature's CL. If the check is successful, you immediately learn any two (your choice) of the following pieces of information: Creature's Base Attack Bonus or attack bonus with a particular attack Any one of the creature's Defense Scores Any one of the creature's Skill modifier The presence of any one special quality or Feat (you choose the special quality or Feat, and the Gamemaster reveals whether or not it is present) You can make a Treat Injury check in place of a Mechanics check to Build Object to create a variety of Poisons, using your knowledge of specialized chemicals. When using this Talent, the Hit Point modifier for crafting is equal to the Poison's Challenge Level (for example, Knockout Drugs (CL 2) have a Hit Point modifier of x2). One dose of Poison is equal in size to a Fine object. The complexity of a Poison is determined by its Challenge Level (CL):", "class": "", "category": "", "costNumeric": null, "treeId": "00cb74839a524276", "tags": ["action_economy", "control", "defender", "droid", "feat_chain", "healing", "investigation", "knowledge", "knowledge_creatures", "leader", "mechanics", "mobility", "new_action", "poison", "scaling", "skills", "slicing", "social", "standard_action", "striker", "support", "survival", "sustained_damage", "swift_action", "talent_chain", "trap", "tree_00cb74839a524276", "uncategorized_talent"], "executionModel": "PASSIVE", "subType": "STATE", "abilityMeta": {"modifiers": [{"target": "defense", "value": 1, "type": "untyped", "predicates": ["attack.when-hit"], "enabled": true, "priority": 500, "description": "Identify Creature"}]}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"swse": {"migratedToState": true, "migrationDate": "2026-03-08T18:22:17.420Z", "detectedPredicates": ["attack.when-hit"]}}}
{"_id": "85fddc83428358ae", "name": "Spontaneous Skill", "type": "talent", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"prerequisites": "Educated", "benefit": "Sometimes you surprise others with your skill. Once per day, you may make an Untrained skill check as though you were Trained in the Skill. Exception: you cannot use this Talent to make an Untrained Use the Force check as though you were Trained in the skill, unless you have the Force Sensitivity feat.", "description": {"value": "Sometimes you surprise others with your skill. Once per day, you may make an Untrained skill check as though you were Trained in the Skill. Exception: you cannot use this Talent to make an Untrained Use the Force check as though you were Trained in the skill, unless you have the Force Sensitivity feat.\n\nYou can select this Talent multiple times; each time you do, you can use it one additional time per day."}, "class": "8c58016e587dd2c7", "costNumeric": null, "category": "Noble", "prerequisitesStructured": {"type": "all", "conditions": [{"type": "talent", "id": "swse.talent.educated"}], "_source": "canonical-csv"}, "treeId": "b5bb4154688c66ab", "tags": ["feat-chain", "noble", "scaling", "striker", "talent-chain"], "executionModel": "PASSIVE", "subType": "STATE", "abilityMeta": {"modifiers": [{"target": "attack", "value": 0, "type": "untyped", "predicates": [], "enabled": false, "priority": 500, "description": "[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Spontaneous Skill"}]}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"swse": {"id": "swse.talent.spontaneous_skill", "migratedToState": true, "migrationDate": "2026-03-08T18:22:17.420Z", "detectedPredicates": []}}}
{"_id": "86565bbe8b8fd1a2", "name": "Force Throw", "type": "talent", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"prerequisites": "Empower Weapon", "benefit": "You can hurl Simple Weapons (Melee), or Advanced Melee Weapons your size or smaller as a Standard Action, treating it as a Thrown Weapon. The Thrown Weapon deals normal weapon damage if it hits.", "description": {"value": "You can hurl Simple Weapons (Melee), or Advanced Melee Weapons your size or smaller as a Standard Action, treating it as a Thrown Weapon. The Thrown Weapon deals normal weapon damage if it hits.\n\nIf the weapon deals piercing or slashing damage, it becomes embedded in your target, remaining there and causing an additional die of damage each round at the end of the target's turn, and also when it is removed (removing the embedded weapon is a Swift Action, and an adjacent ally can remove the embedded weapon for you).\n\nYour target must be within 6 squares of you. The weapon does not automatically return to you, but you can retrieve it with the Move Object Force Power (dealing an additional die of damage in the process, if the weapon is embedded in the target, as above)."}, "class": "289fcf920ef0e184", "costNumeric": null, "category": "Force Adept", "prerequisitesStructured": {"type": "all", "conditions": [{"type": "talent", "id": "swse.talent.empower_weapon"}], "_source": "canonical-csv"}, "treeId": "01e443d93e47f9c4", "tags": ["action_economy", "alchemy", "category_force_adept", "controller", "crafting", "empowerment", "feat_chain", "force", "force_capacity", "force_control", "force_execution", "force_power_synergy", "force_training", "mobility", "mystic", "new_action", "positioning", "ranged", "standard_action", "swift_action", "talent_chain", "tree_01e443d93e47f9c4"], "executionModel": "PASSIVE", "subType": "STATE", "abilityMeta": {"modifiers": [{"target": "attack", "value": 0, "type": "untyped", "predicates": [], "enabled": false, "priority": 500, "description": "[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Force Throw"}]}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"swse": {"id": "swse.talent.force_throw", "migratedToState": true, "migrationDate": "2026-03-08T18:22:17.420Z", "detectedPredicates": []}}}
{"_id": "869168cd679ee5d1", "name": "Weapon Specialization", "type": "talent", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"prerequisites": "Weapon Focus with chosen Exotic Weapon or Weapon Group", "benefit": "Choose a single Exotic Weapon or weapon group with which you are proficient. You gain a +2 bonus on damage rolls with such weapons. If you select Heavy Weapons as the weapon group this Talent applies to, you may also use the Talent with Vehicle Weapon attacks.", "description": {"value": "Choose a single Exotic Weapon or weapon group with which you are proficient. You gain a +2 bonus on damage rolls with such weapons. If you select Heavy Weapons as the weapon group this Talent applies to, you may also use the Talent with Vehicle Weapon attacks.\n\nYou may select this Talent multiple times. Each time you select this Talent, it applies to a different Exotic Weapon or weapon group."}, "class": "f62ca2e639cab614", "costNumeric": null, "category": "Soldier", "treeId": "2e9265a596cc43f7", "tags": ["action-economy", "armor", "battlefield-control", "burst-damage", "damage-reduction", "defender", "leader", "melee", "mobility", "positioning", "scaling", "soldier", "striker", "support"], "executionModel": "PASSIVE", "subType": "STATE", "abilityMeta": {"modifiers": [{"target": "defense.reflex", "value": 2, "type": "untyped", "predicates": ["defense.against-melee", "defense.reflex", "attack.when-hit", "attack.with-melee", "turn.once-per-round"], "enabled": true, "priority": 500, "description": "Weapon Specialization"}]}}, "effects": [{"_id": "f1f96ea3-6139-440c-877a-24fa994deaf4", "name": "Weapon Specialization", "icon": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "changes": [{"key": "system.damage.melee", "mode": 2, "value": "2"}], "disabled": false, "duration": {}, "flags": {"swse": {"source": "talent", "talentName": "Weapon Specialization"}}}], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"swse": {"id": "swse.talent.weapon_specialization", "migratedToState": true, "migrationDate": "2026-03-08T18:22:17.420Z", "detectedPredicates": ["defense.against-melee", "defense.reflex", "attack.when-hit", "attack.with-melee", "turn.once-per-round"]}}}
{"_id": "86a8e796b6c4deae", "name": "Impaling Assault", "type": "talent", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"prerequisites": "Weapon Specialization", "benefit": "You can hit your opponents to slow them down. Whenever you successfully damage an opponent using a Piercing weapon that you have the Weapon Specialization Talent for, your opponent reduces its speed by 2 squares until the end of your next turn. The effects of multiple Impaling Assaults do not stack.", "description": {"value": "You can hit your opponents to slow them down. Whenever you successfully damage an opponent using a Piercing weapon that you have the Weapon Specialization Talent for, your opponent reduces its speed by 2 squares until the end of your next turn. The effects of multiple Impaling Assaults do not stack."}, "class": "f62ca2e639cab614", "costNumeric": null, "category": "Soldier", "prerequisitesStructured": {"type": "all", "conditions": [{"type": "talent", "id": "swse.talent.weapon_specialization"}], "_source": "canonical-csv"}, "treeId": "2e9265a596cc43f7", "tags": ["feat-chain", "mobility", "soldier", "striker", "talent-chain"], "executionModel": "PASSIVE", "subType": "STATE", "abilityMeta": {"modifiers": [{"target": "attack", "value": 0, "type": "untyped", "predicates": [], "enabled": false, "priority": 500, "description": "[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Impaling Assault"}]}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"swse": {"id": "swse.talent.impaling_assault", "migratedToState": true, "migrationDate": "2026-03-08T18:22:17.420Z", "detectedPredicates": []}}}
{"_id": "86c10d63bba2d9c8", "name": "Trigger Work", "type": "talent", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"prerequisites": "", "benefit": "You take no penalty on your attack roll when using the Rapid Shot feat.", "description": {"value": "You take no penalty on your attack roll when using the Rapid Shot feat."}, "class": "162d866ba36fce69", "costNumeric": null, "category": "Gunslinger", "treeId": "cb6f775cd227a3e3", "tags": ["ranged"], "executionModel": "PASSIVE", "subType": "STATE", "abilityMeta": {"modifiers": [{"target": "attack", "value": 0, "type": "untyped", "predicates": [], "enabled": false, "priority": 500, "description": "[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Trigger Work"}]}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"swse": {"id": "swse.talent.trigger_work", "migratedToState": true, "migrationDate": "2026-03-08T18:22:17.420Z", "detectedPredicates": []}}}
{"_id": "86fbb269a17a8c5e", "name": "Masquerade", "type": "talent", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"prerequisites": "Illusion", "benefit": "Use the Force in place of Deception when creating a deceptive appearance.", "description": "Use the Force replaces Deception to create a deceptive appearance.", "costNumeric": null, "prerequisitesStructured": {"type": "all", "conditions": [{"type": "talent", "id": "swse.talent.illusion"}], "_source": "canonical-csv"}, "treeId": "6ac3416fb6aada56", "tags": ["controller", "deception", "feat_chain", "force", "force_execution", "illusion", "skill_substitution", "skills", "social", "social_control", "talent_chain", "telekinesis", "telepathy", "tree_6ac3416fb6aada56", "uncategorized_talent", "use_the_force"], "executionModel": "PASSIVE", "subType": "STATE", "abilityMeta": {"modifiers": [{"target": "attack", "value": 0, "type": "untyped", "predicates": [], "enabled": false, "priority": 500, "description": "[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Masquerade"}]}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"swse": {"id": "swse.talent.masquerade", "migratedToState": true, "migrationDate": "2026-03-08T18:22:17.420Z", "detectedPredicates": []}}}
{"_id": "871638a983029bc4", "name": "Demand Surrender", "type": "talent", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"prerequisites": "Presence", "benefit": "Once per encounter, you can make a Persuasion check as a Standard Action to demand surrender from an opponent who has been reduced to one-half or less of its hit points. If your check result equals or exceeds the target's Will Defense, it surrenders to you and your allies, drops any weapons it is holding, and takes no hostile actions. If the target is higher level than you, it gains a +5 bonus to its Will Defense. If you or any of your allies attack it, it no longer submits to your will and can act normally. You can only use this Talent against a particular target once per encounter. This is a Mind-Affecting effect.", "description": {"value": "Once per encounter, you can make a Persuasion check as a Standard Action to demand surrender from an opponent who has been reduced to one-half or less of its hit points. If your check result equals or exceeds the target's Will Defense, it surrenders to you and your allies, drops any weapons it is holding, and takes no hostile actions. If the target is higher level than you, it gains a +5 bonus to its Will Defense. If you or any of your allies attack it, it no longer submits to your will and can act normally. You can only use this Talent against a particular target once per encounter. This is a Mind-Affecting effect.\n\nUnlike other Mind-Affecting effects, you need only to hail a Vehicle to Demand Surrender. You can demand surrender of a vehicle that has been reduced to one-half or fewer of its hit points, even if the crew is uninjured. You make your check against the Vehicle's Commander; all Nonheroic crews are assumed to have a Will Defense of 10. If the CL of the target Vehicle is greater than your Heroic Level or the CL of your Vehicle, the target gains a +5 bonus to its Will Defense. You can't use this Talent to Demand Surrender from a Vehicle that is more than one size larger than yours under any circumstances- Star Destroyers don't surrender to X-Wings."}, "class": "8c58016e587dd2c7", "costNumeric": null, "category": "Noble", "prerequisitesStructured": {"type": "all", "conditions": [{"type": "talent", "id": "swse.talent.presence"}], "_source": "canonical-csv"}, "treeId": "e99cfa9db8493573", "tags": ["action-economy", "condition-removal", "controller", "feat-chain", "force", "force-control", "force-offense", "leader", "light-side", "mobility", "noble", "positioning", "striker", "support", "sustained-damage", "talent-chain"], "executionModel": "PASSIVE", "subType": "STATE", "abilityMeta": {"modifiers": [{"target": "skill", "value": 2, "type": "untyped", "predicates": ["attack.when-hit", "proximity.ally-nearby", "turn.once-per-round"], "enabled": true, "priority": 500, "description": "Demand Surrender"}]}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"swse": {"id": "swse.talent.demand_surrender", "migratedToState": true, "migrationDate": "2026-03-08T18:22:17.420Z", "detectedPredicates": ["attack.when-hit", "proximity.ally-nearby", "turn.once-per-round"]}}}
{"_id": "874ffa6b66cf2c37", "name": "Reduce Defense", "type": "talent", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"prerequisites": "", "benefit": "When you score a Critical Hit with a melee or ranged attack, your target takes a -2 penalty to their Reflex Defense until it is fully healed (at maximum Hit Points).", "description": {"value": "When you score a Critical Hit with a melee or ranged attack, your target takes a -2 penalty to their Reflex Defense until it is fully healed (at maximum Hit Points)."}, "class": "c4dbedcf989cb6b2", "costNumeric": null, "category": "Elite Trooper", "treeId": "71e99c646b18d85c", "tags": ["defender", "medicine", "precision", "skills", "soldier", "striker", "support"], "executionModel": "PASSIVE", "subType": "STATE", "abilityMeta": {"modifiers": [{"target": "defense.reflex", "value": 2, "type": "untyped", "predicates": ["defense.reflex", "attack.when-hit"], "enabled": true, "priority": 500, "description": "Reduce Defense"}]}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"swse": {"id": "swse.talent.reduce_defense", "migratedToState": true, "migrationDate": "2026-03-08T18:22:17.420Z", "detectedPredicates": ["defense.reflex", "attack.when-hit"]}}}
{"_id": "878d89b7232413cf", "name": "Set for Stun", "type": "talent", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"prerequisites": "", "benefit": "You are particularly adept with Stun weapons. If you are using a ranged weapon that deals Stun damage (including a lethal weapon set to Stun), you can spend two consecutive Swift Actions in the same round to activate this Talent. If the Stun damage on your next attack exceeds the target's Damage Threshold, you move the target -3 steps along the Condition Track, instead of the normal -2 steps.", "description": {"value": "You are particularly adept with Stun weapons. If you are using a ranged weapon that deals Stun damage (including a lethal weapon set to Stun), you can spend two consecutive Swift Actions in the same round to activate this Talent. If the Stun damage on your next attack exceeds the target's Damage Threshold, you move the target -3 steps along the Condition Track, instead of the normal -2 steps."}, "class": "e647ee8f065e1d19", "costNumeric": null, "category": "Infiltrator", "treeId": "7c7a8730e1b4381a", "tags": ["condition-removal", "controller", "mobility", "striker"], "executionModel": "PASSIVE", "subType": "STATE", "abilityMeta": {"modifiers": [{"target": "attack", "value": 0, "type": "untyped", "predicates": [], "enabled": false, "priority": 500, "description": "[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Set for Stun"}]}}, "effects": [{"_id": "1bccc1ff-f9fc-4c04-9b5c-6976b186a80d", "name": "Set for Stun", "icon": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "changes": [{"key": "system.damage.stun", "mode": 2, "value": "2"}], "disabled": false, "duration": {}, "flags": {"swse": {"source": "talent", "talentName": "Set for Stun"}}}], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"swse": {"id": "swse.talent.set_for_stun", "migratedToState": true, "migrationDate": "2026-03-08T18:22:17.420Z", "detectedPredicates": []}}}
{"_id": "8793a955bce166d2", "name": "Illusion", "type": "talent", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"prerequisites": "", "benefit": "As a Swift Action, you can reduce the penalty for large by one half (rounded down, minimum -1). You have a natural ability to use Dark Side artifacts, such as Sith Talismans and alchemical items. Once per encounter, you may spend a Force Point to treat the damage from a Sith Alchemical Weapon as though you had rolled the maximum damage on the dice. Once per encounter, using rudimentary Sith sorcery, you channel Dark Side energy in a manner that boosts one use of a Force Power. As a Swift Action, you can add 1 die of damage (if the Force Power deals damage) or extend the range of the Force Power by 6 squares (if it has a range beyond yourself or a single target). Using this Talent automatically adds the [Dark Side] descriptor to the Force Power used.", "description": "As a Swift Action, you can reduce the penalty for large by one half (rounded down, minimum -1). You have a natural ability to use Dark Side artifacts, such as Sith Talismans and alchemical items. Once per encounter, you may spend a Force Point to treat the damage from a Sith Alchemical Weapon as though you had rolled the maximum damage on the dice. Once per encounter, using rudimentary Sith sorcery, you channel Dark Side energy in a manner that boosts one use of a Force Power. As a Swift Action, you can add 1 die of damage (if the Force Power deals damage) or extend the range of the Force Power by 6 squares (if it has a range beyond yourself or a single target). Using this Talent automatically adds the [Dark Side] descriptor to the Force Power used.", "costNumeric": null, "treeId": "d29a7261c1be4b83", "tags": ["action_economy", "controller", "damage_reduction", "dark_side", "deception", "force", "force_capacity", "force_offense", "force_point_spend", "force_power_synergy", "illusion", "mobility", "positioning", "resource_spend", "striker", "support", "sustained_damage", "swift_action", "tree_d29a7261c1be4b83", "uncategorized_talent"], "executionModel": "PASSIVE", "subType": "STATE", "abilityMeta": {"modifiers": [{"target": "attack", "value": 2, "type": "untyped", "predicates": ["turn.once-per-round"], "enabled": true, "priority": 500, "description": "Illusion"}]}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"swse": {"id": "swse.talent.illusion", "migratedToState": true, "migrationDate": "2026-03-08T18:22:17.420Z", "detectedPredicates": ["turn.once-per-round"]}}}
{"_id": "87c0a929a04eb870", "name": "Vaapad", "type": "talent", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"prerequisites": "Juyo, Weapon Focus (Lightsabers), Weapon Specialization (Lightsabers), Base Attack Bonus +12", "benefit": "When attacking with a Lightsaber, you score a critical hit on a natural roll of 19 or 20. However, a natural 19 is not considered an automatic hit; if you roll a natural 19 and still miss the target, you do not score a critical hit.", "description": {"value": "When attacking with a Lightsaber, you score a critical hit on a natural roll of 19 or 20. However, a natural 19 is not considered an automatic hit; if you roll a natural 19 and still miss the target, you do not score a critical hit."}, "class": "fb5c2644f988e6bf", "costNumeric": null, "category": "Jedi Knight", "treeId": "2bc2572e852832e4", "tags": ["feat-chain", "jedi", "lightsaber", "melee", "positioning", "precision", "striker", "talent-chain"], "executionModel": "PASSIVE", "subType": "STATE", "abilityMeta": {"modifiers": [{"target": "attack", "value": 0, "type": "untyped", "predicates": [], "enabled": false, "priority": 500, "description": "[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Vaapad"}]}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"swse": {"id": "swse.talent.vaapad", "migratedToState": true, "migrationDate": "2026-03-08T18:22:17.420Z", "detectedPredicates": []}}}
