{"_id": "b0898acb0a19a3cd", "name": "Force Flow", "type": "talent", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"prerequisites": "Vital Transfer", "benefit": "You have an extraordinarily strong connection to The Living Force. Whenever you roll a Natural 20 on a Use the Force check, you gain one temporary Force Point. If the Force Point is not used by the end of the encounter, it is lost. You cannot take this Talent if you already possess the Talent, and vice versa. Homebrew Reference Book: Clone Wars Saga Edition Fan Sourcebook - Jedi Masters (Part 2) You possess a natural affinity for using The Force to influence others. Once per encounter, you may spend a Force Point as a Free Action to place any Force Power with the [Mind-Affecting] descriptor into your Force Power Suite, even if you do not normally have that Force Power. If the Force Power is not used before the end of the encounter, it is lost. You may select this Talent multiple times. Each time you select it, you may use this Talent one additional time per encounter. Homebrew Reference Book: Legacy of the Force Sourcebook Once per round, you may choose to reroll a Use the Force check made to activate one of the following Force Powers: Force Disarm, Force Grip, Force Slam, Force Thrust, Move Object, or Repulse. The result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse. Homebrew Reference Book: Clone Wars Saga Edition Fan Sourcebook - The Jedi Order You possess an innate talent with telekinetic manipulation, and uses of the ability come more naturally to you than it does to others. Once per encounter, you may expend a Force Point as a Free Action to use any Force Power with the [Telekinetic] descriptor, even if you do not normally have that Force Power in your Force Power Suite. You may select this Talent multiple times. Each time you select it, you may use this Talent one additional time per encounter. Homebrew Reference Book: Legacy of the Force Sourcebook Once per encounter as a Swift Action, you can expend one of your Force Points to give one ally within line of sight a temporary Force Point. If this Force Point is not used by the end of the encounter, it is lost.", "description": "You have an extraordinarily strong connection to The Living Force. Whenever you roll a Natural 20 on a Use the Force check, you gain one temporary Force Point. If the Force Point is not used by the end of the encounter, it is lost. You cannot take this Talent if you already possess the Talent, and vice versa. Homebrew Reference Book: Clone Wars Saga Edition Fan Sourcebook - Jedi Masters (Part 2) You possess a natural affinity for using The Force to influence others. Once per encounter, you may spend a Force Point as a Free Action to place any Force Power with the [Mind-Affecting] descriptor into your Force Power Suite, even if you do not normally have that Force Power. If the Force Power is not used before the end of the encounter, it is lost. You may select this Talent multiple times. Each time you select it, you may use this Talent one additional time per encounter. Homebrew Reference Book: Legacy of the Force Sourcebook Once per round, you may choose to reroll a Use the Force check made to activate one of the following Force Powers: Force Disarm, Force Grip, Force Slam, Force Thrust, Move Object, or Repulse. The result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse. Homebrew Reference Book: Clone Wars Saga Edition Fan Sourcebook - The Jedi Order You possess an innate talent with telekinetic manipulation, and uses of the ability come more naturally to you than it does to others. Once per encounter, you may expend a Force Point as a Free Action to use any Force Power with the [Telekinetic] descriptor, even if you do not normally have that Force Power in your Force Power Suite. You may select this Talent multiple times. Each time you select it, you may use this Talent one additional time per encounter. Homebrew Reference Book: Legacy of the Force Sourcebook Once per encounter as a Swift Action, you can expend one of your Force Points to give one ally within line of sight a temporary Force Point. If this Force Point is not used by the end of the encounter, it is lost.", "costNumeric": null, "treeId": "6ac3416fb6aada56", "tags": ["action_economy", "controller", "feat_chain", "force", "force_capacity", "force_control", "force_execution", "force_point_spend", "force_power_synergy", "light_side", "mobility", "resource_spend", "scaling", "skill_substitution", "support", "sustained_damage", "swift_action", "talent_chain", "telekinesis", "telepathy", "tree_6ac3416fb6aada56", "uncategorized_talent", "use_the_force"], "executionModel": "PASSIVE", "subType": "MODIFIER", "abilityMeta": {"modifiers": [{"target": "attack", "type": "untyped", "value": 1, "enabled": true, "priority": 500, "description": "Migrated from AE system.attacks"}]}}, "effects": [{"_id": "5cbd0fc1-985f-4af1-a12b-7f4d70e6f5fd", "name": "Force Flow", "icon": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "changes": [{"key": "system.attacks", "mode": 2, "value": "1"}], "disabled": true, "duration": {}, "flags": {"swse": {"source": "talent", "talentName": "Force Flow", "migratedToPassive": true}}}], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"swse": {"id": "swse.talent.force_flow"}}}
{"_id": "b08c8efbea22f604", "name": "Omens", "type": "talent", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"prerequisites": "Findsman Ceremonies", "benefit": "You see Omens in both success and failure. Whenever an ally within 10 squares and line of sight of you rolls a Natural 1 or a Natural 20 on an attack roll, you gain a +2 insight bonus to either your next attack roll made before the end of your next turn, or a +2 insight bonus to your Reflex Defense until the end of your next turn (your choice).", "description": {"value": "You see Omens in both success and failure. Whenever an ally within 10 squares and line of sight of you rolls a Natural 1 or a Natural 20 on an attack roll, you gain a +2 insight bonus to either your next attack roll made before the end of your next turn, or a +2 insight bonus to your Reflex Defense until the end of your next turn (your choice)."}, "class": "336bba6d1e517c92", "costNumeric": null, "category": "Bounty Hunter", "prerequisitesStructured": {"type": "all", "conditions": [{"type": "talent", "id": "swse.talent.findsman_ceremonies"}], "_source": "canonical-csv"}, "treeId": "022b31d355c840a9", "tags": ["defender", "positioning", "scoundrel", "scout", "skills", "striker", "support"], "executionModel": "PASSIVE", "subType": "MODIFIER", "abilityMeta": {"modifiers": [{"target": "defense.fortitude", "type": "untyped", "value": 1, "enabled": true, "priority": 500, "description": "Migrated from AE system.defenses.all"}, {"target": "defense.reflex", "type": "untyped", "value": 1, "enabled": true, "priority": 500, "description": "Migrated from AE system.defenses.all"}, {"target": "defense.will", "type": "untyped", "value": 1, "enabled": true, "priority": 500, "description": "Migrated from AE system.defenses.all"}]}}, "effects": [{"_id": "a60e9429-d125-4d9b-ba92-7fd0a9a17901", "name": "Omens", "icon": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "changes": [{"key": "system.defenses.all", "mode": 2, "value": "1"}], "disabled": true, "duration": {}, "flags": {"swse"