{"_id": "b92e61669b29d090", "name": "Surprise Strike", "type": "talent", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"prerequisites": "", "benefit": "Sometimes a smuggler has to fight his way out of a bad situation. If you fail any Deception check to convey deceptive information, you can initiate combat and make a single Unarmed attack as a Free Action in the Surprise Round (or with a melee or ranged weapon, if you have the Quick Draw feat); all other combatants are considered Surprised even if they are aware of you.", "description": {"value": "Sometimes a smuggler has to fight his way out of a bad situation. If you fail any Deception check to convey deceptive information, you can initiate combat and make a single Unarmed attack as a Free Action in the Surprise Round (or with a melee or ranged weapon, if you have the Quick Draw feat); all other combatants are considered Surprised even if they are aware of you."}, "class": "21dfe84d159a1b7f", "costNumeric": null, "category": "Scoundrel", "treeId": "9f7ca12cc084737a", "tags": ["action-economy", "ambush", "mobility", "scoundrel", "skills", "social", "striker", "sustained-damage", "unarmed"], "executionModel": "PASSIVE", "subType": "STATE", "abilityMeta": {"modifiers": [{"target": "attack", "value": 0, "type": "untyped", "predicates": [], "enabled": false, "priority": 500, "description": "[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Surprise Strike"}]}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"swse": {"id": "swse.talent.surprise_strike", "migratedToState": true, "migrationDate": "2026-03-08T18:22:17.426Z", "detectedPredicates": []}}}
{"_id": "b9c850fce4aa9c55", "name": "Vicious Poison", "type": "talent", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"prerequisites": "Malkite Techniques", "benefit": "Any Poisons you have used against a target gain a +2 bonus to their attack rolls made against that target's Fortitude Defense.", "description": {"value": "Any Poisons you have used against a target gain a +2 bonus to their attack rolls made against that target's Fortitude Defense."}, "class": "21dfe84d159a1b7f", "costNumeric": null, "category": "Scoundrel", "prerequisitesStructured": {"type": "all", "conditions": [{"type": "talent", "id": "swse.talent.malkite_techniques"}], "_source": "canonical-csv"}, "treeId": "c55b003333ff082d", "tags": ["defender", "feat-chain", "scoundrel", "striker", "talent-chain"], "executionModel": "PASSIVE", "subType": "STATE", "abilityMeta": {"modifiers": [{"target": "defense.fortitude", "value": 2, "type": "untyped", "predicates": ["defense.fortitude"], "enabled": true, "priority": 500, "description": "Vicious Poison"}]}}, "effects": [{"_id": "37a21864-2b4e-498c-a4eb-279f320402b8", "name": "Vicious Poison", "icon": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "changes": [{"key": "system.poison.attack", "mode": 2, "value": "2"}], "disabled": false, "duration": {}, "flags": {"swse": {"source": "talent", "talentName": "Vicious Poison"}}}], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"swse": {"id": "swse.talent.vicious_poison", "migratedToState": true, "migrationDate": "2026-03-08T18:22:17.426Z", "detectedPredicates": ["defense.fortitude"]}}}
{"_id": "b9fce171cad543d7", "name": "Clone Scientist", "type": "talent", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"prerequisites": "", "description": "Trained in Knowledge (Life Sciences) You have unlocked the secrets of combining the genes of a variety of creatures to create mutations and even new Species. When you create a gene-spliced clone, first select a DNA template as normal. Next, you may add additional template Species, each time adding either one method of movement, one natural weapon, or one Species Trait or special quality. Every additional Species spliced adds +10 to the cloning attempt DC. Each new form of movement adds +10 to the DC, each new natural weapon/attack adds +5 to the DC, and each Species Trait or special quality adds +10 to the DC. Spliced Traits can stack with and Master Cloner traits. Prerequisites: , Trained in Knowledge (Life Sciences) Prerequisites: , Trained in Knowledge (Life Sciences) When cloning, you may select advanced traits for the clone, listed below. These traits may be selected in tandem with the Clone Scientist Traits, unless stated otherwise. Prerequisites: , Trained in Knowledge (Life Sciences) You have found ways to increase the rate of aging of clones to more quickly put them in service. The overall cost of the creation of the clone is increased by the age modifier. When a clone whose age has been accelerated moves at least -2 steps down the Condition Track in the same encounter, they also add a year to their relative Age. Also note that while accelerated Aging brings the clones to physical maturity more quickly, mentally, they progress at their actual physical age. This means that a Human clone who is engineered to age twice as fast as normal, will be a physical adult after eight years (Humans are Adults at 16-40 years old), giving them no modifiers of a Child to Intelligence, Wisdom and Charisma until they are twelve years old (twenty-four in clone years). Prerequisites: , Master Cloner, Trained in Knowledge (Life Sciences)", "benefit": "Trained in Knowledge (Life Sciences) You have unlocked the secrets of combining the genes of a variety of creatures to create mutations and even new Species. When you create a gene-spliced clone, first select a DNA template as normal. Next, you may add additional template Species, each time adding either one method of movement, one natural weapon, or one Species Trait or special quality. Every additional Species spliced adds +10 to the cloning attempt DC. Each new form of movement adds +10 to the DC, each new natural weapon/attack adds +5 to the DC, and each Species Trait or special quality adds +10 to the DC. Spliced Traits can stack with and Master Cloner traits. Prerequisites: , Trained in Knowledge (Life Sciences) Prerequisites: , Trained in Knowledge (Life Sciences) When cloning, you may select advanced traits for the clone, listed below. These traits may be selected in tandem with the Clone Scientist Traits, unless stated otherwise. Prerequisites: , Trained in Knowledge (Life Sciences) You have found ways to increase the rate of aging of clones to more quickly put them in service. The overall cost of the creation of the clone is increased by the age modifier. When a clone whose age has been accelerated moves at least -2 steps down the Condition Track in the same encounter, they also add a year to their relative Age. Also note that while accelerated Aging brings the clones to physical maturity more quickly, mentally, they progress at their actual physical age. This means that a Human clone who is engineered to age twice as fast as normal, will be a physical adult after eight years (Humans are Adults at 16-40 years old), giving them no modifiers of a Child to Intelligence, Wisdom and Charisma until they are twelve years old (twenty-four in clone years). Prerequisites: , Master Cloner, Trained in Knowledge (Life Sciences)", "class": "", "category": "", "costNumeric": null, "treeId": "8e44e56069274319", "tags": ["biotech", "cloning", "condition_removal", "controller", "crafting", "investigation", "knowledge", "mobility", "scaling", "science", "striker", "support", "tree_8e44e56069274319", "uncategorized_talent"], "executionModel": "PASSIVE", "subType": "STATE", "abilityMeta": {"modifiers": [{"target": "attack", "value": 0, "type": "untyped", "predicates": [], "enabled": false, "priority": 500, "description": "[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Clone Scientist"}]}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"swse": {"migratedToState": true, "migrationDate": "2026-03-08T18:22:17.426Z", "detectedPredicates": []}}}
{"_id": "bab0b5d081e304b6", "name": "Experienced Brawler", "type": "talent", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"prerequisites": "Melee Smash, Stunning Strike", "benefit": "You know how to fight when the odds are against you. You can use each of the following actions as a Standard Action once per encounter:", "description": {"value": "You know how to fight when the odds are against you. You can use each of the following actions as a Standard Action once per encounter:\n\nAvoid Attack: Make a single melee attack against an opponent within your Reach. Until the beginning of your next turn, you gain a +5 dodge bonus to your Reflex Defense against a single attack as a Reaction.\nFortified Mind: Make a single melee attack against an opponent within your Reach. Until the beginning of your next turn, you gain a +5 bonus to either your Fortitude Defense or Will Defense against a single attack as a Reaction.\nFocused Stance: Make a single melee attack against an opponent within your Reach. At any time until the beginning of your next turn, as a Reaction, you can move up to 2 squares. This movement does not provoke Attacks of Opportunity."}, "class": "f62ca2e639cab614", "costNumeric": null, "category": "Soldier", "prerequisitesStructured": {"type": "all", "conditions": [{"type": "talent", "id": "swse.talent.stunning_strike"}], "_source": "canonical-csv"}, "treeId": "67fdd8dce9abd6c1", "tags": ["controller", "defender", "evasion", "feat-chain", "mobility", "positioning", "soldier", "striker", "talent-chain"], "executionModel": "PASSIVE", "subType": "STATE", "abilityMeta": {"modifiers": [{"target": "defense.fortitude", "value": 5, "type": "untyped", "predicates": ["defense.will", "turn.once-per-round"], "enabled": true, "priority": 500, "description": "Experienced Brawler"}]}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"swse": {"id": "swse.talent.experienced_brawler", "migratedToState": true, "migrationDate": "2026-03-08T18:22:17.426Z", "detectedPredicates": ["defense.will", "turn.once-per-round"]}}}
{"_id": "bab9a1ce285f98b9", "name": "Charm Beast", "type": "talent", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"prerequisites": "", "benefit": "You can make a Use the Force check in place of a Persuasion check when attempting to change the Attitude of an undomesticated creature with an Intelligence score of 2 or less. Additionally, you do not take the normal -5 penalty on the check if the creature can't speak or understand your language.", "description": {"value": "You can make a Use the Force check in place of a Persuasion check when attempting to change the Attitude of an undomesticated creature with an Intelligence score of 2 or less. Additionally, you do not take the normal -5 penalty on the check if the creature can't speak or understand your language.\n\nThis Talent is identical to the Dathomiri Witch Talent of the same name, and both are considered to be the same Talent for the purposes of satisfying prerequisites."}, "class": "289fcf920ef0e184", "costNumeric": null, "category": "Force Adept", "treeId": "8a61bf426391431b", "tags": ["action_economy", "battlefield_control", "beast_companion", "category_force_adept", "controller", "defender", "feat_chain", "force", "force_capacity", "force_defense", "force_execution", "force_item", "force_offense", "force_training", "melee", "mobility", "mystic", "persuasion", "positioning", "social", "striker", "support", "sustained_damage", "talent_chain", "tree_8a61bf426391431b", "use_the_force", "weapon_empowerment"], "executionModel": "PASSIVE", "subType": "STATE", "abilityMeta": {"modifiers": [{"target": "defense.reflex", "value": 2, "type": "untyped", "predicates": ["defense.against-melee", "defense.reflex", "attack.with-melee", "movement.while-moving", "proximity.ally-nearby"], "enabled": true, "priority": 500, "description": "Charm Beast"}]}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"swse": {"id": "swse.talent.charm_beast", "migratedToState": true, "migrationDate": "2026-03-08T