{"_id": "bb6511073dfb4774", "name": "Force Delay", "type": "talent", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"prerequisites": "Trained in Persuasion", "description": "Whenever you successfully use , you can grant one ally within 6 squares, and line of sight the ability to trade a Move Action for another Standard Action on their next turn. Jal Shey verbally startle opponents with a little help from The Force. Once per encounter, you can make a Persuasion check against the Will Defense of a target with an Intelligence score of 3 or higher, that can understand you, as a Reaction. If successful, the target loses its Move Action on its next turn. If you choose to spend a Force Point, the target instead loses its Standard Action. You can spend a Force Point to imbue a specifically crafted weapon, armor, or article of clothing with the power of The Force. Imbuing the item requires a Full-Round Action. As a Full-Round Action, the wearer of such an item can open themselves to The Force, transferring one of their Force Points into the item. You can then use a Swift Action to spend a stored Force Point at any later time, even in the same round that you spend a Force Point of your own. You can attune only one item per 24 hours, the item functions only for you, and a given item can only store one Force Point at a time. You cannot wear more than one attuned item at a time, and you can spend only up to a maximum of two Force Points in a round (one of your own, plus one from an imbued item). You can use your scholarly knowledge of The Force to help others reach their full potential. You can spend a Force Point as a Reaction to Aid Another ally within 6 squares on a Use the Force check, following the normal rules for the Aid Another Action as usual.", "benefit": "Whenever you successfully use , you can grant one ally within 6 squares, and line of sight the ability to trade a Move Action for another Standard Action on their next turn. Jal Shey verbally startle opponents with a little help from The Force. Once per encounter, you can make a Persuasion check against the Will Defense of a target with an Intelligence score of 3 or higher, that can understand you, as a Reaction. If successful, the target loses its Move Action on its next turn. If you choose to spend a Force Point, the target instead loses its Standard Action. You can spend a Force Point to imbue a specifically crafted weapon, armor, or article of clothing with the power of The Force. Imbuing the item requires a Full-Round Action. As a Full-Round Action, the wearer of such an item can open themselves to The Force, transferring one of their Force Points into the item. You can then use a Swift Action to spend a stored Force Point at any later time, even in the same round that you spend a Force Point of your own. You can attune only one item per 24 hours, the item functions only for you, and a given item can only store one Force Point at a time. You cannot wear more than one attuned item at a time, and you can spend only up to a maximum of two Force Points in a round (one of your own, plus one from an imbued item). You can use your scholarly knowledge of The Force to help others reach their full potential. You can spend a Force Point as a Reaction to Aid Another ally within 6 squares on a Use the Force check, following the normal rules for the Aid Another Action as usual.", "class": "", "category": "", "costNumeric": null, "treeId": "db1964d1e1d14b5a", "tags": ["action_economy", "armor", "control", "controller", "defender", "delay", "feat_chain", "force", "force_control", "force_defense", "force_execution", "force_point_spend", "investigation", "knowledge", "leader", "mobility", "move_action", "new_action", "persuasion", "positioning", "reaction", "resource_spend", "skills", "social", "standard_action", "support", "sustained_damage", "swift_action", "talent_chain", "tree_db1964d1e1d14b5a", "uncategorized_talent", "use_the_force"], "executionModel": "PASSIVE", "subType": "STATE", "abilityMeta": {"modifiers": [{"target": "defense.will", "value": 2, "type": "untyped", "predicates": ["defense.will", "proximity.ally-nearby", "turn.once-per-round"], "enabled": true, "priority": 500, "description": "Force Delay"}]}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"swse": {"migratedToState": true, "migrationDate": "2026-03-08T18:22:17.426Z", "detectedPredicates": ["defense.will", "proximity.ally-nearby", "turn.once-per-round"]}}}
{"_id": "bc618e6b3da78b3e", "name": "Personal Vendetta", "type": "talent", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"prerequisites": "", "benefit": "As a Swift Action, you can taunt all opponents within 12 squares and line of sight; on their next turn, these opponents take a -2 penalty on attack rolls made against any target other than you.", "description": {"value": "As a Swift Action, you can taunt all opponents within 12 squares and line of sight; on their next turn, these opponents take a -2 penalty on attack rolls made against any target other than you.\n\nThis is a Mind-Affecting effect."}, "class": "533f1066362655c7", "costNumeric": null, "category": "Gladiator", "treeId": "12a2a02b0901605d", "tags": ["controller", "social", "striker"], "executionModel": "PASSIVE", "subType": "STATE", "abilityMeta": {"modifiers": [{"target": "attack", "value": 0, "type": "untyped", "predicates": [], "enabled": false, "priority": 500, "description": "[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Personal Vendetta"}]}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"swse": {"id": "swse.talent.personal_vendetta", "migratedToState": true, "migrationDate": "2026-03-08T18:22:17.426Z", "detectedPredicates": []}}}
{"_id": "bc8667e10d541cb8", "name": "Reactionary Attack", "type": "talent", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"prerequisites": "Born Leader, Trained in Persuasion", "benefit": "Once per encounter, as a Reaction to an attack made against you or an ally, you can direct an ally within 6 squares to make an immediate attack as a Reaction against the attacking enemy. The ally you choose must be capable of making an attack against the target.", "description": {"value": "Once per encounter, as a Reaction to an attack made against you or an ally, you can direct an ally within 6 squares to make an immediate attack as a Reaction against the attacking enemy. The ally you choose must be capable of making an attack against the target."}, "class": "8c58016e587dd2c7", "costNumeric": null, "category": "Noble", "prerequisitesStructured": {"type": "all", "conditions": [{"type": "talent", "id": "swse.talent.born_leader"}], "_source": "canonical-csv"}, "treeId": "5964237d22681dc0", "tags": ["action-economy", "feat-chain", "noble", "positioning", "support", "talent-chain"], "executionModel": "PASSIVE", "subType": "STATE", "abilityMeta": {"modifiers": [{"target": "attack", "value": 2, "type": "untyped", "predicates": ["turn.once-per-round"], "enabled": true, "priority": 500, "description": "Reactionary Attack"}]}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"swse": {"id": "swse.talent.reactionary_attack", "migratedToState": true, "migrationDate": "2026-03-08T18:22:17.426Z", "detectedPredicates": ["turn.once-per-round"]}}}
{"_id": "bca8ce9a488cf3d8", "name": "Shadow Striker", "type": "talent", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"prerequisites": "Hidden Movement, Improved Stealth", "benefit": "You excel at fighting from the shadows, hitting your opponents when they least expect it. You can use each of the following actions once per encounter as a Standard Action:", "description": {"value": "You excel at fighting from the shadows, hitting your opponents when they least expect it. You can use each of the following actions once per encounter as a Standard Action:\n\nBlinding Strike: Make a single melee or ranged attack against an opponent within Range. If you damage the target, you gain Total Concealment against that target until the beginning of your next turn.\nConfusing Strike: Make a single melee or ranged attack against an opponent within Range. If this opponent is denied its Dexterity bonus to its Reflex Defense, or if you have Concealment from this opponent, a successful attack also causes the opponent to be able to take only a Swift Action on its next turn.\nUnexpected Attack: Make a melee or ranged attack within your Range against an opponent from whom you have Concealment. You gain a +2 bonus on this attack roll if you have Concealment, or a +5 bonus if you have Total Concealment."}, "class": "b5bed5d1b5f42958", "costNumeric": null, "category": "Scout", "prerequisitesStructured": {"type": "all", "conditions": [{"type": "talent", "id": "swse.talent.hidden_movement"}], "_source": "canonical-csv"}, "treeId": "3926d582d2077489", "tags": ["action-economy", "defender", "feat-chain", "mobility", "scout", "striker", "talent-chain"], "executionModel": "PASSIVE", "subType": "STATE", "abilityMeta": {"modifiers": [{"target": "defense", "value": 2, "type": "untyped", "predicates": ["turn.once-per-round"], "enabled": true, "priority": 500, "description": "Shadow Striker"}]}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"swse": {"id": "swse.talent.shadow_striker", "migratedToState": true, "migrationDate": "2026-03-08T18:22:17.426Z", "detectedPredicates": ["turn.once-per-round"]}}}
