{"_id": "d26506bfba104470", "name": "Electronic Trail", "type": "talent", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"prerequisites": "Nowhere to Hide, Trained in Use Computer", "description": {"value": "Once you have located a target using Gather Information, you can track its electronic presence. Once per day, you receive a catalog of the target's Electronic Trail, which includes the amount and location of credits spent, the routes of any public transportation taken, and the sites viewed on the HoloNet while the target was logged in using its primary identity.\n\nTo receive this information, you must have access to a computer or Datapad plus access to a network or The HoloNet. This Electronic Trail does not reveal bank balances or other secret information, which requires a separate Gather Information check."}, "benefit": "Once you have located a target using Gather Information, you can track its electronic presence. Once per day, you receive a catalog of the target's Electronic Trail, which includes the amount and location of credits spent, the routes of any public transportation taken, and the sites viewed on the HoloNet while the target was logged in using its primary identity.", "class": "", "category": "", "costNumeric": null, "treeId": "a47ed82a822e3962", "tags": ["action_economy", "defender", "feat_chain", "force", "force_defense", "force_offense", "intel", "investigation", "network", "perception", "sustained_damage", "talent_chain", "tech", "tracking", "tree_a47ed82a822e3962", "uncategorized_talent"], "executionModel": "PASSIVE", "subType": "STATE", "abilityMeta": {"modifiers": [{"target": "defense.fortitude", "value": 2, "type": "untyped", "predicates": ["defense.fortitude", "defense.will"], "enabled": true, "priority": 500, "description": "Electronic Trail"}]}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"swse": {"migratedToState": true, "migrationDate": "2026-03-08T18:22:17.429Z", "detectedPredicates": ["defense.fortitude", "defense.will"]}}}
{"_id": "d2aabaa6848b4a09", "name": "Force Immersion", "type": "talent", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"prerequisites": "", "description": "Whenever you make a Stealth check to Sneak, you can use your check result in place of one adjacent ally's Stealth check to Sneak (additionally, if you have the Talent, that Talent applies to the designated ally as well). Similarly, you can use your Use the Force check result in the place of an adjacent ally's Use the Force check result to avoid detection by the Sense Force application of the skill. You can spend a Force Point to have this ability apply to all adjacent allies instead of just one. As a Reaction to being damaged by an attack or Force Power, you can spend a Force Point to gain Total Concealment from all targets until the end of your next turn. Additionally, if you have not yet taken your Second Wind, you can do so immediately as part of this Reaction. As a Swift Action, you can choose to surrender to the White Current and allow it to flow around you and fuel your Force Powers. Until the end of the encounter, you cannot use Force Powers that do not have \"You\" as the sole target. However, once per turn as a Swift Action, you can recover one spent Force Power that has \"You\" as the sole target without spending a Force Point, adding that Force Power back to your Force Power Suite. You can make a Use the Force check in place of a Stealth check. You are considered Trained in the Stealth skill. If you are entitled to a Stealth check reroll, you can reroll your Use the Force check instead (subject to the same circumstances and limitations).", "benefit": "Whenever you make a Stealth check to Sneak, you can use your check result in place of one adjacent ally's Stealth check to Sneak (additionally, if you have the Talent, that Talent applies to the designated ally as well). Similarly, you can use your Use the Force check result in the place of an adjacent ally's Use the Force check result to avoid detection by the Sense Force application of the skill. You can spend a Force Point to have this ability apply to all adjacent allies instead of just one. As a Reaction to being damaged by an attack or Force Power, you can spend a Force Point to gain Total Concealment from all targets until the end of your next turn. Additionally, if you have not yet taken your Second Wind, you can do so immediately as part of this Reaction. As a Swift Action, you can choose to surrender to the White Current and allow it to flow around you and fuel your Force Powers. Until the end of the encounter, you cannot use Force Powers that do not have \"You\" as the sole target. However, once per turn as a Swift Action, you can recover one spent Force Power that has \"You\" as the sole target without spending a Force Point, adding that Force Power back to your Force Power Suite. You can make a Use the Force check in place of a Stealth check. You are considered Trained in the Stealth skill. If you are entitled to a Stealth check reroll, you can reroll your Use the Force check instead (subject to the same circumstances and limitations).", "class": "", "category": "", "costNumeric": null, "treeId": "4509306f66d744bf", "tags": ["action_economy", "controller", "evasion", "force", "force_capacity", "force_execution", "force_offense", "force_point_spend", "force_power_synergy", "immersion", "mobility", "perception", "positioning", "precision", "reaction", "resource_spend", "scout", "skill_stealth", "skills", "stealth", "striker", "support", "sustained_damage", "swift_action", "tree_4509306f66d744bf", "uncategorized_talent", "use_the_force", "white_current"], "executionModel": "PASSIVE", "subType": "STATE", "abilityMeta": {"modifiers": [{"target": "skill", "value": 2, "type": "untyped", "predicates": ["attack.when-hit", "proximity.ally-nearby"], "enabled": true, "priority": 500, "description": "Force Immersion"}]}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"swse": {"migratedToState": true, "migrationDate": "2026-03-08T18:22:17.429Z", "detectedPredicates": ["attack.when-hit", "proximity.ally-nearby"]}}}
